Name: Minor Overclock Alloy
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a small amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to enhance equipment of Constructs.

Name: Minor Overclock Alloy II
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a small amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to enhance equipment of Constructs.

Name: Minor Overclock Alloy III
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a small amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to enhance equipment of Constructs.

Name: Weapon Overclock Core I
Description: Key material used to increase weapon level limit. Useful for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Basic computing core that increases weapon strength.

Name: Memory Overclock Circuit I
Description: Key material used to increase Memory level limit. Useful for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Basic parts used to expand Memory Chip computing pathways and increase Memory strength.

Name: Major Overclock Alloy
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a large amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to increase the strength of Construct equipment.

Name: Major Overclock Alloy II
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a large amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to increase the strength of Construct equipment.

Name: Major Overclock Alloy III
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a large amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to increase the strength of Construct equipment.

Name: Weapon Overclock Core II
Description: Key material used to increase weapon level limit. Useful for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Advanced computing core that increases weapon strength.

Name: Memory Overclock Circuit II
Description: Key material used to increase weapon level limit. Useful for high-rank Memory.
WorldDesc: Advanced parts used to expand Memory Chip computing pathways and increase Memory strength.

Name: Support Overclock Bundle (S)
Description: A modification bundle prepared for Combat Unit Boosters. It can remove the level limit on low-rank Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: To evolve to the next stage, creatures need to go through substantial hard work and suffering. This also applies to Combat Unit Boosters.

Name: Support Overclock Bundle (L)
Description: A modification bundle prepared for Combat Unit Boosters. It can remove the level limit on high-rank Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: The special tool and material bundle required for further modification of Combat Unit Boosters after they have accumulated sufficient experience.

Name: Support Skill Component
Description: With Combat Unit Booster's skill data loaded, this can increase the skill level of Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: The combat data of Constructs and Combat Unit Boosters is refined and analyzed. By learning such data, the skill module of Combat Unit Boosters can be further optimized.

Name: Frog Accessory
Description: Increases member's Affection. Lucia's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A series of plushies produced by a famous toy-maker brand. Poor sales meant that there are very few of them left.

Name: Biosphere
Description: Increases member's Affection. Liv's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Highly advanced device that holds a self-contained ecosystem, a popular science teaching tool in Babylonia.

Name: Precision Toolkit
Description: Increases member's Affection. Lee's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Toolkit used for the maintenance of electronics.

Name: Jack-in-the-box
Description: Increases member's Affection. Nanami's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Trick box that surprises those who touch it.

Name: Prototype Engine
Description: Increases member's Affection. Karenina's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Simple and powerful, but with a tendency to explode when overloaded - which some people do not see as a flaw.

Name: Portable Game Console
Description: Increases member's Affection. Kamui's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The newest portable game console, perfect for passing the time between missions. Who is behind the anonymous account at the top of the rankings?

Name: MRE Rations
Description: Increases member's Affection. Watanabe's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Popular ration set that contains a main dish, a side course, and coffee. You may even get rare seasoning such as miso if you are lucky.

Name: Lily Brooch
Description: Increases member's Affection. Bianca's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The lily represents selflessness and dignity.

Name: Painting Kit
Description: Increases member's Affection. Ayla's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A painting kit released by the most popular art supply brand "Montpellier", which is dedicated to sharing the happiness of artistic creation to everyone. Montpellier is always an artist's choice.

Name: High-Power Batteries
Description: Increases member's Affection. Sophia's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Batteries for power tools. No mechanics want to find themselves out of batteries during work, right?

Name: R3 Cleaning Robot
Description: Increases member's Affection. Chrome's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Developed by Cosmos Industries for Babylonia's domestic market, this cleaning robot is the best solution to a nice and clean environment.

Name: Military-Grade Bionic Dog
Description: Increases member's Affection. Vera's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A small military-grade bionic dog that performs various functions from item storage to radar detection, with its absolute loyalty to its master being its biggest selling point. It's been widely acclaimed ever since it was released by General Toys.

Name: Media Player
Description: Increases member's Affection. Camu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A peripheral media player device attached to a Construct. Can receive messages and signals from Babylonia.

Name: Weather Glass
Description: Increases member's Affection. Rosetta's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Looking inside this glass bottle can remind you of those snowy nights.

Name: Antique Book
Description: Increases member's Affection. Qu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: This paper-made book is a rare sight when the majority of information is stored digitally. Take extra caution when reading it, for both the content and the book itself are of high value.

Name: Copper Coin
Description: Increases member's Affection. Changyu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Issued by KCC in the Golden Age, this commemorative coin provides a peek into the KCC's prime days. The pattern on it is still clearly visible.

Name: Night Light
Description: Increases member's Affection. Luna's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A small light may dispel darkness from the night. It reminded Luna of those scary nights without her sister or light.

Name: Lunar Tear
Description: Increases member's Affection. 2B, 9S and A2's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A decoration made from rare flowers. It seems to glow under the moonlight.

Name: Hugging Pillow
Description: Increases member's Affection. Wanshi's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: One can find lots of these pillows in Strike Hawk's recovery room. It's soft, simple, and can bring sweet dreams to those using it.

Name: Iris
Description: Increases member's Affection. Selena's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Babylonia seldom wastes resources on ornamental flowers. If you can bring an iris from the surface, put it behind her ear, and you will see a smile more beautiful than the flower.

Name: Audiovisual Terminal
Description: Increases member's Affection. No. 21's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An audio-visual terminal that repeatedly plays various videos, including some programs revived from the golden age. No. 21 seems to be addicted to watching the terminal in her spare time, learning all kinds of content displayed.

Name: Marionette
Description: Increases member's Affection. Roland's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A hand-made puppet that can be moved by a controller. When Roland was an actor, he often used different marionettes to make plays, giving them different identities such as kings, servants, or family. Now he seems to have found someone to walk along in his lone journey.

Name: Panda Change Purse
Description: Increases member's Affection. Pulao's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A cute panda change purse. Pulao used to imagine how it looks like when it's full of Grubs, but unfortunately, it is empty most of the time...

Name: Deluxe Picture Book
Description: Increases member's Affection. Haicma's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A paper picture book published by WGAA with masterpieces of various themes. Haicma loves the diversity of the book, especially the blank page left at the end for the reader to create their own work. Haicma plans to complete it with someone in the future.

Name: Notebook and Pen
Description: Increases member's Affection. Noan's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An ordinary notebook and pen. Noan writes and draws with them.

Name: Music Box
Description: Increases member's Affection. Bambinata's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An exquisite ceramic music box. Once wound up, the music starts and the ballerina comes alive. As long as the music goes on, so too will the ballerina. This is a fragile item. Please handle it with care.

Name: Best-Seller
Description: Increases members' Affection. A common gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Serialized manga that has been a best-seller both on a ground and in Babylonia since the last century, depicting the human struggle against the Punishing Virus.

Name: Vinyl Record
Description: Increases members' Affection. A common gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Specialized teams have been sent to earth to retrieve the sounds, sights and culture that could not be artificially recreated, resulting in this record of a golden era long gone.

Name: Ration Chocolate
Description: Increases members' Affection. An exquisite gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Chocolate bar used as rations by the United Earth military. Has a very long shelf life with a wide variety of flavors. A delicious gift.

Name: 1 Day Tour Tickets x2
Description: Increases members' Affection. An exquisite gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: A pair of bracelet tickets for 2 people to enjoy a day tour of Babylonia, including transport, space observation deck tickets, VIP hologram theater seats, as well as bar and outdoor pool party access.

Name: Normal Gift Box
Description: Gives a random normal gift.
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Fine Gift Box
Description: Gives a random fine gift.
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Precious Gift Box
Description: Gives a random precious gift.
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Sweet Gift Box
Description: Choose 1 from 3 gifts: Precision Toolkit, Portable Game Console, MRE Rations.
WorldDesc: A gift box wrapped with a ribbon. It contains male members' favorite gifts.

Name: Beating Heart Gift
Description: Choose 1 from 6 gifts: Frog Accessory, Biosphere, Jack-in-the-box, Prototype Engine, Lily Brooch, Painting Kit.
WorldDesc: An exquisite gift box that contains female members' favorite gifts.

Name: Crimson Love
Description: Members give this rare collectible to their Commandant on May 20th. It carries special meanings.
WorldDesc: Members have prepared this rose for a special day. It's been carefully sealed within a box so it can be preserved permanently.

Name: White Affection
Description: All members love this rare gift. Give it to them on a special day to create some great memories.
WorldDesc: A customized rose for your important ones. Costs a lot to make, and contains a lot of emotions.

Name: Voice of Thoughts
Description: Gifts given by members to the commandant on May 20 express their strong affection.
WorldDesc: Audiovisual product specifically tailored for commandants. Carefully sealed in a collection box, only special people can open it.

Name: Radiant Comradery
Description: A gift given to members on a special day to express affection and leave a beautiful lasting memory.
WorldDesc: A retro machine that can play audio and video stored on a specific medium. Beneath the elegant shell lies a sincere heart.

Name: S-Rank Character Inver-Shard Pick
Description: Use it in Item > Item.
WorldDesc: Use it to select and get the Inver-Shard of one of the Omniframes: Lee: Entropy, Liv: Luminance, Kamui: Tenebrion, Karenina: Ember, Nanami: Pulse, Lucia: Crimson Abyss, Bianca: Veritas, Lucia: Plume, Rosetta: Rigor, Luna: Laurel, Chrome: Glory.

Name: S-Rank Booster Structural Part Pick
Description: Use it in Item > Item.
WorldDesc: Use it to select and get one of the Booster Structural Parts of the following S-Rank CUBs: Toniris, Frost Oath, and Nitor.

Name: A-Rank Booster Structural Part Pick
Description: Use it in Item > Item.
WorldDesc: Use it to select and get one of the Booster Structural Parts of the following A-Rank CUBs: Yuan Ye, Noctua, Seeshell, Lingya, and Thorny.

Name: Character Upgrade Material Pack
Description: A collection of materials Babylonia specially made for Constructs. Quality and quantity assured.
WorldDesc: Immediately get the following items after use: 6★ Memory Shard x900, Weapon Overclock Core I x28, Weapon Overclock Core II x16, Weapon Enhancer IV x79, Memory Overclock Circuit I x84, Memory Overclock Circuit II x48, Minor Overclock Alloy x80, Major Overclock Alloy x64, Memory Enhancer IV x474, EXP Pod (XL) x25, Skill Point x352, Cogs x5,000,000.

Name: Assessment Manual Shard Choice
Description: Use it in Warehouse > Item.
WorldDesc: Use it to select and get the Inver-Shard of Liv: Luminance or Rosetta: Rigor.

Name: Assessment Manual Shard Choice
Description: Use it in Warehouse > Item.
WorldDesc: Use it to select and get the Inver-Shard of one of the following frames: Liv: Luminance, Rosetta: Rigor, Lee: Entropy, Karenina: Ember, Nanami: Pulse, Kamui: Tenebrion.

Name: Basic Construct R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research Constructs.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access Construct research facilities.

Name: Basic Weapon R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research weapons.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access equipment research facilities.

Name: Basic Memory R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research Memory.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access equipment research facilities.

Name: Target Weapon R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research specific weapons.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access special equipment research facilities.

Name: Target Memory R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research specific Memory.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access special equipment research facilities.

Name: Event Construct R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access Construct research facilities.

Name: Event Weapon R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access special equipment research facilities.

Name: Collab Construct R&D Ticket
Description: Collab item - will be converted into Event Character R&D Ticket upon expiry.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access Construct research facilities.

Name: Collab Weapon R&D Ticket
Description: Collab item - will be converted into Weapon Target R&D Ticket upon expiry.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access special equipment research facilities.

Name: CUB R&D Ticket
Description: The item used to research Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access CUB research facilities.

Name: Collab Construct R&D Ticket
Description: Collab item - will be converted into Event Construct R&D Ticket upon expiry.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access Construct research facilities.

Name: Collab Weapon R&D Ticket
Description: Collab item - will be converted into Targeted Weapon R&D Ticket upon expiry.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access special equipment research facilities.

Name: Secret Pact Card
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access Coating research facilities.

Name: Mermaid's Gift
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to the Task Forces. Accumulate them to access Coating research facilities.

Name: Departure Supply Card
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access research facilities.

Name: Fortune
Description: Use it to purchase items in the [Fortune Merchant] Shop.
WorldDesc: Fortune begets fortune! Collect this Kuroro Charm for the touch of Lady Luck! (*Expires after the event, and you will not be compensated. Please go to the "Fortune Merchant" shop and use it before it expires.)

Name: Fortune Pouch
Description: Use it to try your luck in the [Lucky Draw] event.
WorldDesc: A fat, mysterious pouch! You can definitely seize the good luck in it! (*Expires after the event, and you will not be compensated. Please go to the "Lucky Draw" event and make pulls before it expires.)

Name: Bright Path R&D Ticket
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to the Task Forces. Accumulate them to access research facilities.

Name: Woven Dream's Aurora
Description: A [Dreamcatcher] research event item.
WorldDesc: So long as your memory still exists, so, too, will the magic with which you can make your dreams come true.

Name: Mermaid's Gift
Description: Research event item.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to the Task Force. Accumulate them to access the Coating research facility.

Name: Reagent He-4
Description: Fusion reagent dropped from deep ocean Corrupted. Can be exchanged for items in Frozen Darkness.
WorldDesc: Deep ocean Corrupted store He-4 generated by their internal fusion reactors in special containers, which are considered valuable resources.

Name: Overclock Material Box (α)
Description: Gives a random low-grade overclock material.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Overclock Material Box (β)
Description: Gives a random high-grade overclock material.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Christmas Decor Blueprint Set
Description: Gives 1 random Christmas Blueprint
WorldDesc: A fine Christmas gift box. No way to know which blueprint is inside without opening it.

Name: Heteromer Sample
Description: A sample of Hetero-matter produced by Hetero-Core that can be used in exchange for supplies in Aerial Supply.
WorldDesc: Hetero-derivatives are produced by the Punishing Virus under special environmental conditions. Dense and solid in texture, its behaviors are far more complicated than that of Punishing Virus.

Name: Space Station Battlelog
Description: A battlelog from the space station that can be used in exchange for Battlelog Reward.
WorldDesc: This battlelog not only records and summarizes the combats that occurred every day but also helps you figure out how to enrich Construct's combat experience and skills... Someone said and took out a precious Space Station Battlelog Collector's Edition.

Name: Heteromer Crystal
Description: Raw material for Heteromer Layer Experiment. Conduct Heteromer Layer Experiment to get the Research supplies from Babylonia.
WorldDesc: The pure nucleus formed because of the large structure fluctuation of liquid Hetero-matter. The top-tier scientists of Babylonia are dedicated to the study of Hetero-Core through Heteromer Crystal.

Name: Akdilek Coin
Description: Currency issued by Akdilek that can be used in exchange for items in the event shop.
WorldDesc: With a high level of trading proficiency, Akdilek Commercial Alliance has turned Akdilek Coin into a currency that is even more valuable than rare metals in various regions. Now it is one of the most popular currencies for trading.

Name: Magnetic Ticket
Description: Eternal Throne Abyss Pass (returns 6★ Memory Shard x10 when expired)
WorldDesc: A brand new first-class magnetic ticket with an Akdilek logo and station number. It can be used to enter certain special regions.

Name: Royal Token
Description: A royal token from Asslam that is given as a reward for outstanding merit. Can be used in exchange for corresponding rewards.
WorldDesc: If one can earn respect and trust from the aristocrats on the train, this rare token will be offered as the highest honor given by them.

Name: Support Point
Description: Support permit issued by Babylonia. Can be used to apply for different supports from Babylonia during the mission.
WorldDesc: To support commandants' operation, Babylonia provides support points that can be used to request different supports from Babylonia without President's authorization.

Name: Halloween Candy
Description: Halloween candies provided by Babylonia. Give them to good kids.
WorldDesc: Use it to increase the power of Pet: Michael in Book of Toro.

Name: Toro Coupon
Description: This Babylonia-issued voucher has Commandant's image printed on it. Use it to ask Babylonia for advanced support during your mission.
WorldDesc: Babylonia issued this certificate in order to assist the operations of commandants. It can provide better than usual support when used.

Name: Metal Grub
Description: A currency circulating around the Nighter. Can be used in the Virtual Mart.
WorldDesc: Even when separated, the offspring of the mythological water-beetle qingfu will always return to their mother. Issued by the KCC, the qingfu coin is a symbol of accumulating wealth. Also called grub by the locals.

Name: Holographic Ticket
Description: Cornered in Cruise - Abyss Pass (returns 6★ Memory Shard x10 when expired)
WorldDesc: The first class ticket issued by Kowloong Chamber of Commerce. Use it to watch a holographic puppet show of the performance troupe up close.

Name: Electronic Stamp
Description: Issued by the financial department of KCC, this Electronic Stamp has "Qu" printed on it and can be exchanged for items via the terminals.
WorldDesc: The Electronic Stamps backed by the leader of KCC, "Qu", are proofs of transactions on the Nighter. It serves as both an ID and a trade credit across all the financial terminals.

Name: Titanium Token
Description: Forged from titanium extracted from scrapped mechanical parts, this token is chosen as a widely circulating currency in the microchip market for its lightness and corrosion resistance.
WorldDesc: A new alloy currency issued under the authorization of Asimov, this token is only available in the Memory Chip market. It also works as an ID and a certificate of the Memory Chip knowledge, and is necessary for the purchase of any high-spec components.

Name: Crystal Note
Description: A currency circulating in Kowloong Metropolis. Can be exchanged for items in Kowloong Market.
WorldDesc: An easy-to-carry, ultra slim transaction card issued by Bank of Kowloong. Made from semi-transparent micro crystals, this card has a micro-photon chip inside. A complicated circuit-like glowing pattern is printed on its surface. —"Bank of Kowloong specializes in everything."

Name: Dragon Jade
Description: Dragon Jades are only produced in Kowlong City. They can be exchanged for items in Rosary Path.
WorldDesc: A glossy jade pendant with a vivid floating dragon carved on it. Rumor has it that some mysterious merchants would offer a fortune for this luxurious token...

Name: Morning Star Cup
Description: Randomly dropped in event stages that have a Serum cost. Can be exchanged for Sorbet Summer event mission rewards.
WorldDesc: The Venus Splash Park limited edition ice-cream cup. Ticket holders can get a free cup from A'Mao. Made from strawberries, chocolate flakes, cream, and a paper card of Shark-speare. Note: The paper is not edible.

Name: Square Chip
Description: Can be used to flip one tile in Summer Flip.
WorldDesc: An exquisite square chip, used as a token for the wildly popular board game in the central arcade in Venus Splash Park. Win a certain amount of them and you get to take home all the prizes sealed away in the glass cabinet. Want to try your luck?

Name: One-Point Dice
Description: Can be used in Summer Flip. Allows you to select a reward icon and move it one tile.
WorldDesc: A beautifully crafted six-sided dice, used in the board game in the central arcade of Venus Splash Park. All its six sides bear the same number: "1"—so no matter how you throw it, you will always wind up moving one step.

Name: Heat Mixture
Description: A currency circulating around the Arctic Route Union. Can be used in the Snow Depot.
WorldDesc: Issued by the Arctic Route Union. One of the common supplies that humans living in the arctic region rely on. Quickly heats up upon use.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 1
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 2
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 3
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 4
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 5
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 6
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 7
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 8
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Dream Shard
Description: Use it to purchase items from the Elegy Of Nightmare event shop.
WorldDesc: The bionic mind model that carries traces of information about Amberia after decoding.

Name: Tranquilizer
Description: Use it to participate in the Elegy Of Nightmare event.
WorldDesc: A special tranquilizer designed to treat potential M.I.N.D. deviation after going deep into the bionic network for too long. (Tranquilizers automatically recover every day. Can be used in the Elegy Of Nightmare event.)

Name: Promotion Certificate
Description: Use it to star up members in Mycenaean Protocol.
WorldDesc: Provided by the Mycenaean Protocol, this electronic certificate allows commandants to temporarily increase the member's access level.

Name: Modification Points
Description: Points earned by members after the team levels up in the Mycenaean Protocol. Used for special modification.
WorldDesc: A temporary modification quota under the Mycenaean Protocol that allows commandants to adjust battle strategies where necessary.

Name: Glowstick
Description: Use it to express your support in [Potato's Attack! Support Solon Lee!] event.
WorldDesc: Rumor has it that one can power up the entire team by holding this glowstick up and shaking it... Oh, please don't shake your terminal.

Name: Team Merit
Description: The EXP value used to upgrade team level in Mycenaean Protocol.
WorldDesc: Provided by the Mycenaean Protocol, this electronic certificate allows commandants to temporarily increase their team's access level.

Name: Charter Panel
Description: Ticket for participating in the Chained Simulation event.
WorldDesc: The data panel records the details of the specifications of the simulation. You should confirm all the precautions in the panel before starting. (It is issued automatically at 7:00 UTC every day)

Name: Buff Chip
Description: It is used to increase EXP of Buff level in the Chained Simulation event.
WorldDesc: This special chip can improve the simulation efficiency, providing new Buff ideas for combat. (Obtained after first clear)

Name: Cheering Stick 2023
Description: Materials used to express support in the event of "Festival Battleground: The Legendary Battle Between Red and Blue!"
WorldDesc: Not only are they good-looking batons, but they can also contribute to the team they support.

Name: Modification Points
Description: Evaluation points in Limit Break that record stage-related modification information
WorldDesc: In the end, only cold numbers can represent everything, and this is an exploration of the boundaries of all abilities.

Name: Modification Points
Description: Evaluation points in Limit Break that record stage-related modification information
WorldDesc: In the end, only cold numbers can represent everything, and this is an exploration of the boundaries of all abilities.

Name: Ultralimit Points
Description: Points accumulated in the Ultimate Brawl mode

Name: Compressed Energy Source
Description: Energy can be used to amplify Super Cores. Obtained by challenging opponents in the Ultimate Brawl.

Name: Leap Blueprint
Description: Blueprint used to star up Super Cores. Obtained by challenging the opponents in the Ultimate Brawl for the first time.

Name: Remnant Data Vault
Description: A data set used to upgrade team level. Obtained by from first clear of Ultimate Brawl.
WorldDesc: The analysis and integration of key data from defeated enemies can help enhance our understanding of the enemy.

Name: Tactical Notes
Description: An item for Corrupted Waves character upgrade

Name: Remnant Record
Description: Use it to upgrade Defensive Devices and hunting add-ons in Winter Sequence.
WorldDesc: The observer records every step along the way.

Name: Seal of Collectibles
Description: Carved by the Qiuniu Crew of KCC, this seal can be exchanged for rare items from the Ancient Archive.
WorldDesc: A square seal with a metal-looking texture. KCC's leader, Qu, stored a large amount of cultural relics in the Ancient Archive. Anything marked with this seal would be a rare collectible.

Name: Bipolar Crystal
Description: A bipolar storage made from special materials. Use it to obtain items in "Backlight Matrix."
WorldDesc: Made from special materials, this crystal storage can bring back dusted oaths and memories. Light flows inside the crystal, giving a brilliant shine.

Name: Hetero-Creature Sample
Description: Separated from the host and tightly sealed, this Hetero-creature is still undergoing rapid transformation. It must be handled by specialist teams.
WorldDesc: Researchers are collecting samples from different regions for cross-comparison in order to find out why Punishing Virus has developed biological traits.

Name: Holy Hymn
Description: A flexible crystal formed from special materials. Use it to obtain items in "Heavenly Gift."
WorldDesc: Formed from special materials, this flexible crystal can help to recover dusted oaths and memories. There are divine chants echoing around it, singing hymns of blessing.

Name: Reinforcing Chip
Description: A data program that can improve the exploration ability of the Connector and unlock new talents.
WorldDesc: Loaded with data of many skills, it can unlock the Connector's various abilities.

Name: Battle Support Points
Description: Can be exchanged for various supplies from the shop.
WorldDesc: A temporary currency issued by Babylonia for large-scale ground warfare. Can be exchanged for special combat supplies.

Name: Exploration EXP
Description: Represents a squad's performance records. Accumulate EXP to increase exploration rating.

Name: Stamina
Description: In-depth exploration may significantly consume the Stamina of Connector.
WorldDesc: Stamina has a limit and is restored at 5:00 daily. You must consume Stamina to pass certain checks.

Name: Cleansing Unit
Description: Removes 1 random negative effect from 1 Connector. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (13): "Might enemies are often feared, but ignoring your own sub-optimal condition can be more fatal."

Name: Integrated Cleansing Module
Description: Removes all negative effects from 1 Connector. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (27): "Always ensure all squad members engage in their best condition."

Name: Powered Suit
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Combat ability by 1 within today. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (3): "Do not blindly believe in your strength. It doesn't mean everything."

Name: Powered Suit EX
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Combat ability by 2 within today. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (4): "But absolute power can overwhelm everything!"

Name: Recon Wingman
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Perception ability by 1 within today. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (5): "Modern wars are essentially wars of intelligence."

Name: Wide-area Recon Wingman
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Perception ability by 2 within today. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (31): "Victory comes from knowing you and your enemy. Loss is often a result of limited vision."

Name: Processing Unit
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Arithmetic ability by 1 within today. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (33): "A calm mind means faster and more accurate decisions."

Name: Overclock Processing Unit
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Arithmetic ability by 2 within today. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (8): "An army's best performance is limited by strategic thinking, while actual tactics lay the necessary foundation in the worst situation."

Name: Energy Potion I
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Combat roll by 3 within 1 round. Carry limit: 10
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (12): "Focus all your available strength is the key when facing a formidable enemy."

Name: Energy Potion II
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Combat roll by 6 within 1 round. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (10): "Always use a familiar weapon if you can. Strange gadgets often lead to quick death."

Name: Energy Potion III
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Combat roll by 9 within 1 round. Carry limit: 3
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (9): "The strength of an individual or an army is limited. Learn to utilize all available resources."

Name: Sensor Enhancing Liquid I
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Perception roll by 3 within 1 round. Carry limit: 10
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (17): "Do not miss any details on the battleground. They may not be able to always save your life, but sometimes they can."

Name: Sensor Enhancing Liquid II
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Perception roll by 6 within 1 round. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (37): "A wise general cherishes precious information, but such information would only bring fear and hesitation to fools."

Name: Sensor Enhancing Liquid III
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Perception roll by 9 within 1 round. Carry limit: 3
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (46): "An ordinary commander reads information. A good commander uses the information. A talented commander would create information."

Name: Processor Amplifier I
Description: Increases 1 Connector's Arithmetic roll by 3 within 1 round. Carry limit: 10
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (23): "Always remember to think before you move."

Name: Processor Amplifier II
Description: Increases one Connector's Arithmetic roll by 6 within 1 round. Carry limit: 5
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (21): "All battles are essentially games. Good strategies often come out better even if they are played late."

Name: Processor Amplifier III
Description: Increases one Connector's Arithmetic roll by 9 within 1 round. Carry limit: 3
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (40): "There is no need to find a perfect solution. The battlefield is always rapidly changing. What's perfect at this moment may kill you in the next second."

Name: Initialization Module
Description: Resets all tactical enhancement modules.
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (20): "Sometimes, emptying yourself and relearning everything can get you completely different answers."

Name: Re-calculation Order
Description: Allows 1 Connector to calculate again.
WorldDesc: Tactical Advice (43): "Use the re-calculation order with great caution. It gives you a second chance, but there is no such thing in real wars."

Name: Short-range Jet
Description: Unlocks [B01 Junction Corridor] Lv.3 Area

Name: Lucia's Will
Description: Unlocks [Core Area] Power Room
WorldDesc: I am... Lucia!

Name: Ruolin's Video
Description: Unlocks [B01 Junction Corridor] Lv.4 Area
WorldDesc: She's saying 'thank you' to you...

Name: Lamia's Location
Description: Removes the blockade on the Open Land of [Shattered Valley]
WorldDesc: You found Lamia!

Name: Hetero-Creature Footprints
Description: Removes the blockade on the Open Land of [Shattered Valley]
WorldDesc: Follow the footprints of Hetero-creature and quietly move forward.

Name: Body Fluid of Hetero-Creature
Description: Removes the blockade on the Open Land of [Shattered Valley]
WorldDesc: The Hetero-creature's body fluid left some traces behind. Follow the traces to find it.

Name: Run-away Mermaid
Description: Removes the blockade on the Open Land of [Shattered Valley]
WorldDesc: Lamia is not far ahead. Don't let her get away!

Name: Facing the Polyphage
Description: Removes the blockade on the Open Land of [Shattered Valley]
WorldDesc: You finally confronted the Polyphage.

Name: Split Second Opportunity
Description: Removes the blockade on [Polyphage Left Hand] Lv.1 Area
WorldDesc: There was a weakness in the Hetero-creature's siege for one split second.

Name: Defense Compromised
Description: Removes the blockade on [Polyphage Left Hand] Lv.1 Area
WorldDesc: Successfully hacked into the defense system and disabled it.

Name: Determination
Description: Removes the blockade on [Polyphage Core] Lv.1 Area
WorldDesc: The violent shock gradually stopped. Your determination helped you to prevail.

Name: Final Stretch
Description: Removes the blockade on [Polyphage Core] Lv.1 Area
WorldDesc: You dodged the Polyphage's counterattack, and successfully crossed the last stretch of road.

Name: Scrapped
Description: Removes the blockade on the Open Land of [Shattered Valley]

Description: A data fragment of unknown origin. Activates [Blasphemy]

Name: Data Fragment - Adverse Impact
Description: A data fragment of unknown origin. Unlocks [Polyphage Left Hand] Lv.2 Area

Name: Recording Fragment N1
Description: Removes the blockade on [Polyphage Core] Lv.1 Area
WorldDesc: A broken recording. It could help to uncover some hidden past.

Name: Hidden Video - Engraver
Description: An encrypted video. Use it to activate [Engraver].

Description: Remove the blockade on [Polyphage Core] Lv.2 Area
WorldDesc: A broken recording. It could help to uncover some hidden past.

Name: Deep Memory Shard - Ember
Description: A Memory Shard encrypted using complicated methods. Extract it to uncover some dusted memories.
WorldDesc: Someone will remember.

Name: Deep Memory Shard - Answers
Description: A Memory Shard encrypted using complicated methods. Extract it to uncover the truth hidden under lies.
WorldDesc: Does it matter if the answer is true or false? He is only moving toward the light, right at this moment.

Name: Black Card
Description: Sell it in [Warehouse - Others] for Cogs
WorldDesc: A token issued by Nanami government. You can buy many fun things with it! So don't sell it!

Name: Commandant 99★ Exclusive Weapon
Description: Use it in [Warehouse - Consumable]. Gives Serum×60.
WorldDesc: An individual weapon of a unique style. It provides all attacks except for firepower attacks.

Name: Super Special Serum
Description: Use it in [Warehouse - Consumable]. Gives Serum×60.
WorldDesc: A serum made by careful Noctis with the serum sample provided by kind Vera and packed by lovely No. 21. It's more effective than normal serum.

Name: Pink Letter
Description: Use it in [Warehouse - Consumable]. Gives Serum×60.
WorldDesc: The red lip print gives off an aroma of roses. The pink paper creates a romantic atmosphere. It's said that it was sent by the fifth person of Strike Hawk, the one that is "always on the Commandant's mind."

Name: Stomach Medicine?
Description: Use it in [Warehouse - Consumable]. Gives Serum×60.
WorldDesc: Heals all bitterness until you meet the one that is second to none.

Name: Generic Processor
Description: Increases the level of POD.
WorldDesc: A generic auxiliary computing processor. Install it on a POD to enhance its processing power.

Name: Empty Record
Description: Automatically recovers 3 at 07:00 AM UTC everyday.
WorldDesc: A type of data storage. It can be converted into another form by writing data to it.

Name: EXP-A2
Description: Increases the level of A2 in [YoRHa Archive].
WorldDesc: It seems to enhance the performance of YoRHa Type A No.2.

Name: EXP-9S
Description: Increases the level of 9S in [YoRHa Archive].
WorldDesc: It seems to enhance the performance of YoRHa No.9 Type S.

Name: EXP-2B
Description: Increases the level of 2B in [YoRHa Archive].
WorldDesc: It seems to enhance the performance of YoRHa No.2 Type B.

Name: Modification Part
Description: Increases the level of [POD Skill].
WorldDesc: A part used in the modification of POD.

Name: Broken Coin
Description: Use it in [Secret Exchange].
WorldDesc: A broken coin of unknown origin. It seems to be used as a currency in some place.

Description: Automatically recovers 3 at 5:00 everyday.

Name: Kuroro Cleaner Prototype
Description: This prototype was abandoned due to a built-in AI error, but when Celica finally found out, it had already quietly manufactured tens of thousands units.
WorldDesc: All of them escaped the workshop before they were destroyed, and later showed up in various popular locations. Recycle them in Temp Imbalance to earn supplies rewards—all of which would be coming from the technicians who were supposed to look after the production line.

Name: Temp Imbalance Tape
Description: A souvenir received from taking part in Temp Imbalance. Once obtained, it will be converted into Temp Imbalance Collectible.
WorldDesc: Defeat all the obstacles to seize the victory. The best commandant of Babylonia will never lose! Records Commandant's outstanding performance on Crabsgiving Day. Also has Celica's autograph on it.

Name: Temp Imbalance Tape
Description: A souvenir received from taking part in Temp Imbalance. Upgrades the Temp Imbalance Collectible to blue.
WorldDesc: Defeat all the obstacles to seize the victory. The best commandant of Babylonia will never lose! Records Commandant's outstanding performance on Crabsgiving Day. Also has Celica's autograph on it.

Name: Temp Imbalance Tape
Description: A souvenir received from taking part in Temp Imbalance. Upgrades the Temp Imbalance Collectible to purple.
WorldDesc: Defeat all the obstacles to seize the victory. The best commandant of Babylonia will never lose! Records Commandant's outstanding performance on Crabsgiving Day. Also has Celica's autograph on it.

Name: Temp Imbalance Tape
Description: A souvenir received from taking part in Temp Imbalance. Upgrades the Temp Imbalance Collectible to orange.
WorldDesc: Defeat all the obstacles to seize the victory. The best commandant of Babylonia will never lose! Records Commandant's outstanding performance on Crabsgiving Day. Also has Celica's autograph on it.

Name: Coupon
Description: This prototype was abandoned due to a built-in AI error, but when Celica finally found out, it had already quietly manufactured tens of thousands units.
WorldDesc: All of them escaped the workshop before they were destroyed, and later showed up in various popular locations. Recycle them in Temp Imbalance to earn supplies rewards—all of which would be coming from the technicians who were supposed to look after the production line.

Name: Incomplete Fragment
Description: Storage chip found in various places of X-51 facility. It stores unknown data.
WorldDesc: The data inside is highly fragmented, but you may be able to combine sufficient chips to obtain more complete data blocks.

Name: Yan
Description: One of the Spring Characters. Complete [Lucky Hammer] and [Festival Missions] to get random Spring Characters, and collect all four of "Yan", "Rang", "Ying", and "Sui" to redeem a reward.
WorldDesc: Forms part of a traditional festival greeting phrase "Yan Rang Ying Sui, Tu Su Nuan Chun", which was used in an ancient Eastern country during the Golden Age. It translates to "Let the spirits guide us to a prosperous new year, as we enjoy wine in a warm spring."

Description: One of the Spring Characters. Complete [Lucky Hammer] and [Festival Missions] to get random Spring Characters, and collect all four of "Yan", "Rang", "Ying", and "Sui" to redeem a reward.
WorldDesc: Forms part of a traditional festival greeting phrase "Yan Rang Ying Sui, Tu Su Nuan Chun", which was used in an ancient Eastern country during the Golden Age. It translates to "Let the spirits guide us to a prosperous new year, as we enjoy wine in a warm spring."

Name: Empty Paper
Description: Obtained via [Lucky Hammer] and [festival missions]. Can be used as any character to redeem rewards.
WorldDesc: You can write anything on this empty rice paper... Probably.

Name: Yan Rang Ying Sui
Description: Collect all four characters of "Yan Rang Ying Sui" to redeem this gift. Open it to get training materials such as Cogs and Enhancers.
WorldDesc: A gift that can be redeemed after collecting certain four characters that form a couplet. It contains pleasant surprises.

Name: Tu Su Nuan Chun
Description: Collect all four characters of "Tu Su Nuan Chun" to redeem this gift. Open it to get training materials such as Cogs and Enhancers.
WorldDesc: A gift that can be redeemed after collecting certain four characters that form a couplet. It contains pleasant surprises.

Name: New Year Box
Description: Only those who have collected "Yan Rang Ying Sui" and "Tu Su Nuan Chun" may claim this ultimate gift. Contains great rewards such as Black Cards and limited Spring Festival Memories.
WorldDesc: A special gift given to people during the traditional festival in an ancient Eastern country back in the Golden Age. Rumor has it that the recipients would be blessed by a mysterious power.

Name: Silver Hammer
Description: Use this heavy hammer to attack the Fortune Giver and obtain points.
WorldDesc: Nanami found this toy in a shopping center. It seems to be a popular Golden Age movie merchandise.

Name: Golden Hammer
Description: This shiny hammer is even heavier than the silver one. It has a higher chance to knock out the Fortune Giver.
WorldDesc: Nanami found this toy in a shopping center. It seems to be a popular Golden Age movie merchandise.

Name: Awakened Lion
Description: This charm contains a hidden power. After using it, you have a 150% chance to knock out the Fortune Giver.
WorldDesc: Embroidered with an awakened lion, this spring souvenir commemorates an entertainment performance popular in the Golden Age.

Name: Fortune Lion
Description: This charm contains a lucky power. After using it, you have a 200% chance to knock out the Fortune Giver.
WorldDesc: Embroidered with a fortune lion, this spring souvenir commemorates an entertainment performance popular in the Golden Age.

Name: Lock Charm
Description: A lock infused with the power of protection. It prevents points loss even after a failed attempt.
WorldDesc: This nicely made lock is called "Ping'an Suo" (lock of safety) in the Eastern culture. Nobody knows where Nanami found it.

Name: Lucky Money
Description: Mysterious points found on the Fortune Giver. It can be exchanged for something else in the New Year Store.
WorldDesc: A red envelope issued by the Fortune Giver on the special festival. Look at its exclusive logo, exquisite shape, and premium feel! Note: Fortune Giver reserves all rights for final explanation.

Name: Fortune Character Bag
Description: Contains one random Spring Character in the [Spring Collection] event.
WorldDesc: Available for sale in the shopping district of Babylonia, each of this special Spring Festival bag has one random character inside. "Life is like a lucky bag; you never know what's inside the next one."

Name: Basic Operator
Description: You can recruit members and buy bonuses at normal and challenge difficulty levels, and you can raise the upper limit of operators when you clear normal difficulty stages.
WorldDesc: Contains Construct-related data and a basic combat log unit. Can be used multiple times without reset. All consumed operators will be returned regardless of the challenge result.

Name: Simulated Operator
Description: You can recruit members and buy bonuses at normal and challenge difficulty levels, and you can get an abundant of operators when you clear challenge difficulty stages and complete daily missions.
WorldDesc: Provides the user with diverse combat support and simulation. Must be reset each time after use. All consumed operators will be returned if the challenge fails, but not after a successful challenge.

Name: Simulation Module
Description: The log of data module generated based on the battle result.
WorldDesc: Clear Restrain Simulation stages under normal difficulty to obtain this data log. Collect a certain number for supplies rewards. All supplies are provided by the experiment organizers.

Name: Surface Sample
Description: Local soil specimen collected near the domain nodes. Can be exchanged for rewards in the Analysis Lab.
WorldDesc: This sample is collected from the desert ground to help researchers understand the rise and fall pattern of the Red Tide. Closely sealed for transport.

Name: Sound Tuner
Description: Can be used to unlock different Add-ons. More powerful parts require more to unlock.
WorldDesc: Old and broken parts. New parts can be made by reading the voices inside.

Name: Song Fragment
Description: Can be used to activate different Add-ons. Higher level parts require more fragments to activate. Obtained from Daily Rewards.
WorldDesc: Lost information fragments with a chance to be recovered after collecting some.

Name: Festival Stamp
Description: Used to increase the contestant's Cheer Points in Eden Festival. There is a daily limit to the number of votes that can be used for each contestant in different sessions.
WorldDesc: Use Festival Stamps to participate in the activities held by your favorite contestant, and vote to support them! Using 1 Festival Stamp can add 1 Cheer Point to the contestant.

Name: True Love Stamp
Description: In the Eden Festival, vote for the contestant with Ture Love Stamps to add to their Cheer Points without voting limit.
WorldDesc: True love is unstoppable! Use True Love Stamp to participate in the activities held by your favorite contestant, and vote to support them! Using 1 True Love Stamp can add 10 Cheer Points to the contestant.

Name: Special Stamps
Description: In the Eden Festival, vote for the contestant with Special Stamps to add to their Cheer Points without voting limit.
WorldDesc: There are some special stamps, but it doesn't matter, they can all be used to participate in the activities held by your favorite contestant, and vote to support them! Using 1 Special Stamp can add 1 Cheer Point to the contestant.

Name: Joy
Description: Obtain by voting during the voting period, and can be used to draw mystery boxes at the Tea Stall.
WorldDesc: Besides ordinary whistle, it can also blow sweet music. A nameless whistle which was named "Joy" at the suggestion of Nanami. Hope everyone who participates in the Festival can harvest relaxed and cheerful memories like whistles.

Name: Preparation Feedback
Description: In the Festival Preparation period, you can claim corresponding rewards when you get a certain amount of preparation feedback every day. It is reset when at 07:00 (UTC) every day.
WorldDesc: For the smooth holding of the Festival, everyone's hard work will not be in vain! In order to thank those who worked hard together, the organizers prepared various rewards in return.

Name: Cheer Supplies
Description: During the Festival Preparation mode, give it to Helpers to increase their Mood.
WorldDesc: Cheer Supplies collected in preparation for the festival. Apparently, they can be used to rejuvenate the spirit of others.

Name: Subsequent Implementation Constructs
Description: Subsequent Implementation Welfare of Eden Festival
WorldDesc: Subsequent Implementation Welfare of Eden Festival

Name: Subsequent Implementation Portrait Frame
Description: Subsequent Implementation Welfare of Eden Festival
WorldDesc: Subsequent Implementation Welfare of Eden Festival

Name: Subsequent Implementation Communication Video
Description: Subsequent Implementation Welfare of Moe War
WorldDesc: Subsequent Implementation Welfare of Moe War

Name: Golden Days
Description: During the Cultural Festival voting, obtain by using stamps to vote. Exchange for previous nameplates in the Remembrance Parlor.
WorldDesc: Special currency said to be produced by Celica for Eden Festival (2023).

Name: Festival Stamp (2023)
Description: Used in Eden Festival (2023) to increase Cheer Points for contestants. Each session gives different amount of Festival Stamps for players to use to vote.
WorldDesc: Use Festival Stamps to participate in events organized by your favorite special someone. Work together to increase their Cheer Points during the Festival. Giving 1 Festival Stamp equals 1 Cheer Point.

Name: True Love Stamp (2023)
Description: During Eden Festival (2023), use True Love Stamps to vote for contents and increase their Cheer Points. Additionally, there is no limit to the number of stamps that can be given.
WorldDesc: True love is unstoppable! Use True Love Stamps to participate in events organized by your favorite special someone. Work together to increase their Cheer Points during the Festival. Giving 1 True Love Stamp equals 10 Cheer Points.

Name: Special Stamp (2023)
Description: During Eden Festival (2023), use Special Stamps to vote for contents and increase their Cheer Points. Additionally, there is no limit to the number of stamps that can be given.
WorldDesc: A specially made stamp that can be used to participate in events organized by your favorite special someone. Work together to increase their Cheer Points during the Festival. Giving 1 Special Stamp equals 1 Cheer Point.

Name: Joy (2023)
Description: Obtained while voting during the festival event. Exchange at the tea stall for mystery boxes.
WorldDesc: The whistle made at the request of Nanami during the first Eden Festival has become a token of the Cultural Festival. This was suggested with the hope that everyone can create memories as happy and joyful as the whistle during the event.

Name: Puzzle Chromatography Card
Description: Obtained from the Puzzle Missions and can be used to participate in the Basic Puzzle event.
WorldDesc: The cipher card used to participate in the Number Puzzle. You will feel full of strength and hope when holding the card. This is a game with fate and is the turning point of success or failure.

Name: Puzzle Analysis Card
Description: Obtained from the Puzzle Missions, and can be used to participate in the Premium Puzzle event.
WorldDesc: The special cipher card used to participate in the Number Puzzle. You will feel full of strength and hope when holding the card. This is a game with fate and is the turning point of success or failure.

Name: Frequency Response Map
Description: The structure simulation map of the underground waterway that can be exchanged for materials at the Spectrum Analysis Center.
WorldDesc: Information on fork roads and flow direction obtained when scouts explore the underground waterways with active sonar equipment. It is the data needed to analyze the structure of the underground water network.

Name: Button Cell
Description: It is used to purchase goods in the Poker Guessing Event Shop.
WorldDesc: The small battery can provide a considerable amount of power in a pinch. It seems to have undergone complex procedures to prevent children from ingesting it. Caution is advised—do not taste it.

Name: City Leaflet
Description: These damaged city leaflets can be used to exchange materials in the shop.
WorldDesc: Slightly damaged, the city leaflet records local news and global events. You may be able to piece together some of the past events from the countless shredded fragments.

Name: Cup Noodle
Description: Cup noodles favored by researchers. Can be used to exchange for items in the [Kyaranta Storage].
WorldDesc: The most common instant food overworked researchers turn to. It can satisfy the stomach, but not the taste buds. The dust that have settled on the outside are tears of loneliness of the forgotten cup noodle.

Name: Tainted Name Tag
Description: A dirty, tainted name tag. Can be exchanged for items in [Logistics].
WorldDesc: This standard name tag seems to have been damaged in battle. The engraving on its surface, as well as the identity data stored inside, have been badly damaged.

Name: Prayer Spark
Description: Can be used to exchange for supplies via [Shop Packaging]. May the stars and sparks guide you in the darkness.
WorldDesc: Everyone's hope, persistence, struggles, and tears have become the sparks of prayer in Liv's M.I.N.D., whose light might be tiny but shine eternally just like Liv's will.

Name: Celestial Bamboo Shoot
Description: A bamboo shoot that emits a soft glow. Use these bamboo shoots to exchange for items in the [Celestial House Grocery Store].
WorldDesc: A celestial bamboo that grows with the essences of heaven and earth and can prolong life — Sounds like a local ad catchphrase.

Name: Star Scar
Description: The residual light of a falling star. Use it to exchange for items in [Alternative Dimension].
WorldDesc: A flicker of light created when a star is shattered. It measures and reveals the changes of energy all the time.

Name: Birth Memento
Description: A carefully preserved screw. Use it to exchange for items in the [Mysterious Sanctuary].
WorldDesc: With the first screw embedded, the metal starts to develop a soul. Machines often see the screw as a memento of their birth.

Name: Condensed Electron Pair
Description: Sealed experimental material that can be exchanged for items at [Research Center 042].
WorldDesc: Experimental materials for condensed matter physics. It is indispensable for the study of zero energy, but manufacturing and collecting takes considerable effort.

Name: Dream Firefly
Description: Can be exchanged for items in [Warehouse G54].
WorldDesc: A mechanical firefly in the dream. Unlike the one in real life, it doesn't have any scars on the body. Use it to exchange for supplies <//memories> stored in Warehouse G54.

Name: Crystal Seashell
Description: Use it to exchange for supplies in [Seaborne Trading Post].
WorldDesc: An empty shell crystallized from an unknown mineral. It's not sure if the complex spiral pattern is carrying a mysterious message.

Name: Uniform Bowtie
Description: An old but well-cleaned bowtie. Can be exchanged for supplies in the [Charity Shop].
WorldDesc: It was provided along with the uniform for every child back in the orphanage, reminding them of the importance of keeping up their manners.

Name: Cooperation Merit
Description: Awarded to participants of the Command Bureau challenges and managed by the Commander-in-Chief and Deputy Commander. It can be spent to purchase resources in a specific shop.
WorldDesc: Obtained by participating in the Command Bureau events. It showcases the merits earned by the Command Bureau.

Name: Time-Frozen Hourglass
Description: It can serve as tokens used to purchase items from the Spiraling Time Shop.
WorldDesc: Slipping through the fingers of the god of time, the sand converges into a flower bud of red and gold. Lost traveler, do you still remember the lighthouse that guides you on the way?

Name: Dream Snare
Description: Once picked, this nameless flower can be exchanged for items in the Painted World.
WorldDesc: Flourishing only in the Painted World, this flower's flawless beauty is a reflection of the girl's dream. Even if it is just an illusion, she stills wants to witness the blooming moment.

Name: Tactical Pouch
Description: Used to expand the Add-on Inventory in Deep Blue Warzone. 1 Pouch increases the capacity of the Inventory by 1 and is applied automatically when obtained.
WorldDesc: A pouch that can be carried by Constructs.

Name: Data Track
Description: Event token used to exchange for supplies in Tactical Supply in Deep Blue Warzone. Obtained from the Infinite Abyss and Challenge Stages.
WorldDesc: Formless memory that manifested as Data Track, proving that all the battles fought were not just a figment of your imagination.

Name: Add-on Essence
Description: Exchange for Add-ons at the Add-on Fusion Center. Obtained from scrapping Add-ons.
WorldDesc: The core part of Add-on data.

Name: Add-on Fusion Center
Description: Exchange Add-on Essence for Add-ons at the Add-on Fusion Center.
WorldDesc: There are no excess resources in this world. Learn to use all that is available if you want to win.

Name: Ultralimit Simulation
Description: Increase character Ultralimit LV and Stats by using Add-ons.
WorldDesc: Overclocking is always risky, but you need not worry here.

Name: SP Character
Description: Each week, some characters would receive DMG Bonus.
WorldDesc: There is no strongest soldier, only those who can adapt can survive.

Name: Multi-teams Challenge
Description: Challenge Stage requires multiple teams.
WorldDesc: The battlefield is always changing, utilize multiple small teams to conquer the field.

Name: Special Enhancement
Description: Consume specific parts to unlock specific character Buffs.
WorldDesc: Sometimes, one soldier who has mastered their art can make a whole difference on the battlefield.

Name: Special Serum
Description: Use it to clear the Special Dispatch blocks. It will automatically restore over time.
WorldDesc: A kind of Immune Serum specially made for the environment on the ground.

Name: Trial Prototype
Description: Use it to exchange for items in Special Dispatch - Special Supplies.
WorldDesc: A broken prototype device waiting for collection on the battleground.

Name: Amplification Sequence
Description: Use it to raise Tactical Amplification Level. Amplification Level upgrade will improve team's base stats in the battle and unlock more bonuses to equip.
WorldDesc: A lost Tactical Sequence. Recycle and analyze it to enhance the user's stats.

Name: Liv: Empyrea
Description: Clearing it will grant Liv: Empyrea trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Name: Karenina: Ember
Description: Clearing it will grant Karenina: Ember trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Name: Nanami: Pulse
Description: Clearing it will grant Nanami: Pulse trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Description: Clearing it will grant Roland: Flambeau trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Description: Clearing it will grant Liv: Luminance trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Description: Clearing it will grant Lucia: Crimson Abyss trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Name: Lucia: Plume

Name: Chrome: Glory
Description: Clearing it will grant Chrome: Glory trial character, which can be used for battle and dispatch in Special Dispatch, and the character will gain Battle Amplification.

Name: Gleaming Thread
Description: Can be used to flip cards in event [Afterglow of Fate].
WorldDesc: A fine thread from the World Cocoon. The fairy used these threads to wave the fate of all beings.

Name: Primordial Crystal
Description: Can be exchanged for items in the [Tree of Life] shop.
WorldDesc: A clear crystal with small glittering light in it.

Name: Set Plank
Description: A wood plank stained with paint. Can be used to exchange for items via the [Souvenir Merchant].
WorldDesc: A wood plank used in WGAA of Babylonia. Even though most of the scenes and effects can be done with hologram technology, physical handmade stage decorations like this also have their significance.

Name: Enhanced Red
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Red Orbs by 50% for 2 turns. Cooldown: 6 turns (Amplified: Increases the Damage Points of Red Orbs by 100% for 3 turns. Energy Cost: 18)

Name: Enhancement Pick
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Select one type of Orbs and increase their Damage Points by 50%. Cooldown: 3 turns (Amplified: Randomly generate Enhanced Red/Yellow/Blue Orb 30%/40%/50% Damage Point Increase Buff 3 times. Energy Cost: 26)

Name: Change 1 Orb
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Change the color of 1 Orb. Cooldown: 6 turns (Amplified: Change the color of 1 type of Orbs. Energy Cost: 18)

Name: Clear One Column
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Clear one column. Cooldown: 3 turns. (Amplified: Clear one row and one column. Energy Cost: 15)

Name: Swap Orb
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Swap two random Orbs. Cooldown: 6 turns. (Amplified: Swap two random Orbs. The effect could stop upon the 4th swap. Energy Cost: 24)

Name: Clear Same Color
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Remove all Orbs of the designated color. Cooldown: 7 turns (Amplified: Remove all Orbs of the designated color, and it will be counted as a Multiple-Ping during Damage Points calculation. Energy Cost: 14)

Name: Bonus Move
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Add 1 Move. Cooldown: 6 turns (Amplified: Reduce the cooldown of the skills in cooldown by 5 turns. Energy Cost: 22)

Name: Random Ping
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Ping 1 random Orb after each ping. Cooldown: 2 turns (Amplified: Ping 1 Orb. Energy Cost: 4)

Name: Enhanced Blue
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Blue Orbs by 50% for 2 turns. Cooldown: 6 turns (Amplified: Increases the Damage Points of Blue Orbs by 100% for 3 turns. Energy Cost: 18)

Name: Enhanced Yellow
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Yellow Orbs by 50% for 2 turns. Cooldown: 6 turns (Amplified: Increases the Damage Points of Yellow Orbs by 100% for 3 turns. Energy Cost: 18)

Name: Enhanced Basic Attack
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Basic Attack Orbs by 50% for 2 turns. Cooldown: 6 turns (Amplified: Increases the Damage Points of Basic Attack Orbs by 100% for 3 turns. Energy Cost: 18)

Name: Clear One Row
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Clear one row. Cooldown: 4 turns. (Amplified: Clear two rows. Energy Cost: 15)

Name: Change 1 Type of Orbs
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Change the color of 1 type of Orbs. Cooldown: 8 turns (Amplified: Change 20 of the falling Orbs to the specified color. Energy Cost: 30)

Name: Energy Boost
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Grants 15 Energy. Cooldown: 8 turns.

Name: Energy Boost
Description: This Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Energy Boost

WorldDesc: Changes the color of Orbs. Cooldown: 12 turns.

Name: Temporary Item
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Swap two Orbs. Cooldown: 5 turns.
