Name: Pulao: Dragontoll
Description: Unlocks mode characters during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Pulao: Dragontoll—All orbs deal 70% more DMG for 2 turns.

Name: Bianca: Veritas
Description: Unlocks mode characters during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Bianca: Veritas—All orbs on the board will be dissolved with 400% DMG.

Name: Noan: Arca
Description: Unlocks mode characters during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Noan: Arca—Creates 4 random bombs. Upon explosion, they will dissolve the orbs within their corresponding range with 600% DMG.

Name: Chrome: Glory
Description: Unlocks mode characters during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Chrome: Glory—Removes all negative effects on the board.

Name: Lucia: Plume
Description: Unlocks mode characters during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Lucia: Plume—Resets all subskills' cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Red
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Red Orbs deal 50% more DMG for 2 turns. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Blue
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Blue Orbs deal 50% more DMG for 2 turns. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Yellow
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Yellow Orbs deal 50% more DMG for 2 turns. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Basic Attack
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Basic Attack Orbs deal 50% more DMG for 2 turns. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Targeted Enhancement
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: A type of orb can be selected to increase its DMG by 50% for 1 turn. 3-turn cooldown.

Name: Cross Slash
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Dissolves all the orbs in a row and column the selected orb belongs to. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Color Eliminator
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Dissolves all orbs of a designated color. 7-turn cooldown.

Name: Shapeshift
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Changes the color of a type of orb. 8-turn cooldown.

Name: Space Manipulation
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Swaps 2 orbs. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Extra Endeavor
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Able to act one more time. 6-turn cooldown.

Name: Pinpoint Shot
Description: Unlocks skills during the Circuit Connect - Force Unleashed event.
WorldDesc: Dissolves an orb. 2-turn cooldown.

Name: Plum Envelope
Description: Obtained by completing the first mission of the Plum Snow event. Hand it to Celica in the stage to unlock stage hints.
WorldDesc: Pocket money for Celica.

Name: Snowman
Description: Collectible
WorldDesc: A delicate handicraft that represents missing thoughts that will never melt.

Name: Simulacrum Spiral
Description: Can be exchanged for rewards from Recycling Arrangement.
WorldDesc: Traces that show the unconscious thoughts have been intertwined. Acknowledged or not, they are parts of the inner self.

Name: Memory Synapse
Description: Used for Perception Amplification. Can be exchanged for in the Fusion Center.
WorldDesc: A foothold of perception to integrate, reach, and touch something hidden deeper.

Name: Perception Amplification
Description: Once unlocked, the team's combat capabilities can be amplified by spending Memory Synapses.
WorldDesc: Unlocked after completing 5km Zone Operation.

Name: Simulacrum Association
Description: Once unlocked, special stages can be challenged by spending Perception Signal.
WorldDesc: Unlocked after completing 20km Zone Operation.

Name: Fusion Center
Description: Memory Synapses can be exchanged for Add-ons here.
WorldDesc: Unlocked after completing 70km Zone Operation.

Name: Diffusing Sense Memories
Description: Expands a character's load. Automatically consumed once obtained.

Name: Augmented Sense Memory
Description: Expands the limit of Perception Amplification. Automatically consumed once obtained.

Name: Hypertune Material Pack
Description: Gives Hypertune Crystal α x480 and Hypertune Crystal β x80.
WorldDesc: Contains the materials needed to complete a Hypertune

Name: Hypertune Crystal α
Description: Use it to purchase Hypertune materials (α) from the Hypertune Shop.
WorldDesc: Extracted and reforged from Hypertune materials (α), this crystal coin is a commonly used token in the Hypertune Shop.

Name: Hypertune Crystal β
Description: Use it to purchase Hypertune materials (β) from the Hypertune Shop.
WorldDesc: Extracted and reforged from Hypertune materials (β), this crystal coin is a commonly used token in the Hypertune Shop.

Name: Condelina Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: The Torch of Thinking — Where the original copy of this great work was found is still unknown, but age has taken its toll on the book and it is now hardly interpretable. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Condelina Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Pure Reason — A lengthy, sophisticated masterpiece of philosophy that laid the foundation of many great theories in the old world. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Shakespeare Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Incomplete Scripts — Fragments of an old-world theater play, with some touching stories written on them. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Shakespeare Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Summer Night's Dream — A story about an interesting incident caused by naughty fairies on a summer night. Seems to be highly popular in the old world. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Heisen Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Replica Circuit — A mass-produced replica circuit that took reference from the human brain. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Heisen Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Precision Circuit — A highly sophisticated, precision-machined electronic circuit. Even great scholars would take a lengthy time to study and understand its structure. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Darwin Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: The Outline of Evolution — An outline that resembles a mind map of early-age studies on the origin of creatures. Albeit very brief, it still clearly demonstrates the intelligence of its author. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Darwin Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Abstracts of the Origin of Species — A scientific theory that brought revolution to biology and is still used as an evidence of evolution until today. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Hanna Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Crude Piano Model — A crude model of a mini-piano made out of concepts that still requires a significant amount of work. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality

Name: Hanna Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Wood Piano Model — Crafted from pure timber, this mini-piano model looks so real that one can almost press its keys to play a song. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Cottie Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Doughnut (Low Sugar) — An ordinary-looking low sugar dessert. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Cottie Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Doughnut Box — A gift box consisting of doughnuts made by pastry chefs all around the globe. The doughnuts inside look great and taste delicious without being too sweet. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Da Vinci Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Sketch of Machines — A passionate machine enthusiast's sketch of some mechanical concepts, ranging from basic robots to powered vehicles. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Da Vinci Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Da Vinci's Cryptex — An encrypted tube consisting of 5 rotating alphabetic discs. Rumor has it that secrets are stored inside the tube, but breaking it by force will destroy its content forever. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Catherine Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Flower Bud — This bud was made into a dry specimen before it bloomed so it could be preserved longer. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Catherine Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Red Blossom — A new sample of fresh red rose. Its rotating petals and juicy red color are still highly sought after by many collectors. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Einsteina Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Unfinished Works — An excerpt paying tribute to the original author's academic philosophy, but incomplete for some unknown reason. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Einsteina Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Theory of Relativity (Abstract) — A theory that revolutionized physics and is still seen as the pinnacle of wisdom today. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Philip II Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Silver Alloy Flute — A beautifully crafted flute that is also corrosion resistant, making it a decent option for flute enthusiasts. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Philip II Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Pure Platinum Flute — Its delicate looks suggest an expensive price tag for this hand-crafted instrument. The pure, bright timbre gives the listeners a refreshing feel. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Guinevere Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Glamorous Shard — This timeworn shard used to be part of some luxurious ornament and had witnessed a great but pitiful time. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Guinevere Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Laurel Crown — A corona weaved from laurel leaves for the beauty. It gives a nice fragrance. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Frederick Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Unnamed Music Sheet — No one knows what this simple and pleasant music is called, or where it comes from. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Frederick Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Flute Concerto — This renowned concerto is elegant, passionate and bold, yet has great attention to detail. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Bathlon Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Rusty Badge — This timeworn badge no longer shines, but the honor it carries has not faded a bit. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Bathlon Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Gem Scepter — Crafted from precious metals, this scepter is decorated with many gems, and has a flying eagle carved on the disc at the top. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Patton Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Silver Medal — Forged from silver alloys, this medal is often awarded to those who have made outstanding contribution in one or more areas. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Patton Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Royal Medal — On this medal are lions, unicorns, and a shield in the center. Only those who are kind, brave, and have made great contribution can receive this honor. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Chen Jiyuan Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Measuring Tools — Various types of advanced measuring tools that are easy to carry and manufacture, yet have great precision. Form part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Chen Jiyuan Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Mathematics Collection — A collection of many mathematics models and their solutions that represents the development of mathematics over time, and still has great significance in precision calculation and measuring. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Koya Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Life Support Set: A toolbox once used by Koya. Contains various tools that can be used for combat support, defense fortification, and emergency rescue. Accounts for a section of the chip's signal spectrum and can be used to upgrade the chip.

Name: Koya Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Mottled Photo: A photo of two young boys, one blue-haired and one blond. Their faces, bathed in the sunset glow, are barely invisible. This item accounts for a section of the chip's signal spectrum and can be used to upgrade the chip.

Name: Leeuwenhoek Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Microscope Component — A set of tools that Leeuwenhoek often carried with him. With the look of a classic monocle, it has all the functions needed and can be easily put inside the pocket without you worrying about losing it. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Leeuwenhoek Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Espresso — 30ml of espresso extracted over 28 seconds, made from water at 92 degrees Celcius. With no milk or sugar added and a strong aroma, this used to be Leeuwenhoek's favorite when he had to work overtime, but Asimov strongly disliked it. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Wu'an Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Heavy Chains — These chains would immediately crush any well-trained soldier, but Wu'an put them on himself to control his overwhelming strength. Nobody understands how he survived them. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Wu'an Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Semi-Dry Yellow Wine — Wu'an's favorite drink before going to war. The bottle looks a bit worn-out from countless battles, but the wine within still looks crystal clear and gives a rich aroma. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Flamel Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Type FNII Potion — A medical potion with unknown ingredients that is sealed inside Flamel's personal floating terminals. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Flamel Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Uniform Bandage — Medical bandage manufactured in early Post-Pandemic Age with some battle marks on it. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Lucrezia Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Silver Hair — A strand of silver hair sealed inside a test tube that seems to emit a mysterious fragrance. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Lucrezia Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Sealed Letter — A secret letter sealed with wax with "To Lucrezia" written in cursive on the envelope. No one knows what is actually in the letter. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Exupery Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Planetary painting—painting that can spray planetary patterns is mostly sprayed outside the aircraft, which is the source of some signal frequency bands in the chip and can improve the quality of the chip.

Name: Exupery Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Fox's note—a paper notebook printed with foxes and roses, with such a line written on the front page—"May you find that unique rose." It is the source of part of the signal frequency band in the chip, which can improve the chip quality.

Name: Tifa Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Standardized sewing kit—a sewing kit part of the standardized issued equipment for Task Force members. It is not usually used by members but because Tifa always tears her clothes during battle, she requests new ones periodically. It is the signal source of the chip and can be used to increase the quality of the chip.

Name: Tifa Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Black ribbon—a silky ribbon which Tifa loved to use as an accessory on her cuffs. Although when asked why, she never answers. It is the signal source of the chip and can be used to increase the quality of the chip.

Name: Jack Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Toy Gun—"Bang!" This toy gun can shoot a white flag. It is often used by "Jack" in films to mock the cowards begging for his mercy. Unfortunately, his laughter can be more deadly than bullets. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Jack Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Gentleman's Hat — A gentleman must always stay elegant. An appropriate, well-designed hat is a must-have accessory for gentleman, as well as the most symbolic attire of "Jack" as a character. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Elizabeth Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Infusion Stand — A common life-sustaining apparatus at the patient's bedside. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Elizabeth Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Medic Nameplates — She keeps the nameplates of every medic she parted from. With them, one can read the case history of all the patients the medics treated in the Star of Life terminal... This is how these lives are remembered. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Seraphine Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Maid Uniform — A common blue and white maid uniform during the Golden Age. It has witnessed Seraphine's past. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Seraphine Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Natural Pigment — An ancient pigment made from animal blood and grass juice. It is said to be used by Seraphine. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Marco Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Logistics Book — Logistics are the lifeblood of business. The secret in this book has the power to disrupt a country's economy. It's the source of part of a chip's signal frequency band and can improve a chip's quality.

Name: Marco Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Chiwen Jade Pendant — A jade pendant owned by Kowloong Chiwen Crew. Whoever holds it can divert all external ports and reserve funds for emergency matters. It grants infinite trust and a huge responsibility. It's the source of part of a chip's signal frequency band and can improve a chip's quality.

Name: Unimate Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Retro Glasses—Ordinary optical glasses made durable with advanced technology.

Name: Unimate Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Origin Gear—An item from the memorial. Carried by the primary generation of robots, it is a small piece of gear that is considered redundant in physical terms. However, Unimate insists to have it in the body, as he believes that some things will not be eliminated by time.

Name: Isabel Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Audio Journal—a portable military-grade audio recorder Isabel used to record her journal.

Name: Isabel Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Dawn Medal—a sapphire medal awarded to commemorate Isabel's outstanding contribution. Isabel often wore it, but it's not out of the purpose of showing off. On the contrary, she believed that glory, emotion, thinking, and civilization should not be bound by the material world.

Name: Boone Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Special Bionic Suit—Tailored clothing to maintain warmth and improve comfort. Most importantly, it's less likely to draw the attention of animals. Allowing one to blend in with the environment.

Name: Boone Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Air Dried Sausage—Handmade sausage that requires no complex packaging or additives. It has a unique flavor and can be enjoyed as a snack when food stocks are plentiful. When there is not enough food, you can throw them into a pot to cook for stew.

Name: Shelley Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Broken Pen—Shelley's favorite pen. It's covered with traces of time, but when Shelley holds it in his hand, it becomes the most romantic piece of art and the most powerful weapon.

Name: Shelley Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Origami Boat—A paper boat with a poem written on it. Shelley loves to put these paper boats into the river and watch them float downstream. For him, poetry is the ideal of his life, which will be freed in a faraway place.

Name: Charlotte Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: A lipstick — Charlotte always wears bright lipstick just to stand out from her low-key Purifying Force colleagues. It is the source of her confidence.

Name: Charlotte Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Crimson Blade — Charlotte's favorite Levi-Blade. It was originally a standard Levi-Blade, but Charlotte colored it into her signature crimson red to let the color stay in the memory of her victims forever.

Name: Turing Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: The Enigma Decipher Code is a code Turing created to crack the Enigma machine used for information encryption in information warfare before the Golden Age. By transforming it into a portable decryption key, he made tremendous contributions to the world's subsequent peace process.

Name: Turing Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: The Turing machine is an abstract machine invented by Turing. To put it simply, it is a computation model. Its invention provided the main structure of programming languages for computers from the late Golden Age to break through their computing power limits.

Name: Hypertune Catalyst α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Generates a highly volatile catalytic reaction in the Memory Chip's internal compounds which leads to the forming of low-level bonds between micro particles. Part of the new Memory signals are formed during the reaction.

Name: Hypertune Catalyst β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Generates an extremely volatile catalytic reaction in the Memory Chip's internal compounds which leads to the forming of high-level bonds between micro particles. New Memory signals are rapidly formed during the reaction.

Name: Benizakura
Description: Fairy Garment — Katana
WorldDesc: A katana used by the Performer Puppets to perform an ethereal blade dance.

Name: Iris
Description: Fairy Garment — Bow
WorldDesc: Beautiful things come with thorns, the same as this bow does.

Name: Firecrackers
Description: Spring Festival — Cannon
WorldDesc: Its design is inspired by firecrackers. The firecrackers on the tail can be loaded into the barrel as a projectile. It has a several second downtime after every shot.

Name: Danza Macabra
Description: Hallow Collection — Danza Macabra
WorldDesc: A high-chromium alloy greatsword themed after the festival of the dead. Robust, simple, and rough in design. Fit for a robust, simple, and rough user.

Name: Caldwell - 49
Description: Oathbound — Levi-Gun
WorldDesc: This Levi-Gun was named after a rose in a far-off galaxy. The universe was dubbed the "ultimate romance" during the Golden Age. Of course, converting the romantic value into damage is far more gratifying. Whether it is the aesthetic or the damage rate, it is nearly flawless, except that it demands the user to have a superb aiming skill.

Name: White Acclaim
Description: Oathbound — Bow
WorldDesc: As the name suggests, this is a ceremonial rather than a practical weapon. Instead of a raging battlefield, it belongs in a sacred or peaceful setting.

Name: Thorn Aria
Description: Corrosion — Amplifier
WorldDesc: A powerful amplifier with an eye-catching appearance. When wielded, it creates the illusion of falling stars while amplifying undeniably awe-inspiring damage.

Name: Star of Bethlehem
Description: Christmas — Greatsword
WorldDesc: A greatsword that resembles a Christmas tree. The Star of Bethlehem is stuck tightly on the tip, so tight that not even a fierce swing can shake it off. The blade is not sharp, but its bulk makes it a deadly weapon.

Name: Starry Clouds
Description: Spring Festival — Uniframe Glaive
WorldDesc: The stars have been witnessing mankind for an eternity. The human history is like ever-changing clouds. The patterns on the heavy glaive are delicate and give an antique feel. According to the Kowloong history, this glaive was once given to its owner as a gift. There is a small "Yuan" signed at the end of the letter found in the package.

Name: Lupercalia
Description: Affection — Katana
WorldDesc: Brings the power of the faun's blade to life using modern technology. Inside this chocolate box is the name of your destined one. The ancient reign is long gone, but this bizarre tradition still exists. Come, find your fate in this box. You have unlimited time.

Name: Yggdrasil
Description: Legend — Spear Shield
WorldDesc: As the hero protects this world, the sacred world tree comes to its guardian's aid. Taking a branch from Yggdrasil, the hero turns it into the eternal divine spear—a deadly weapon, as well as a living part of Yggdrasil.

Name: Lion Glory
Description: Yesterday Once More — Gunblade
WorldDesc: Lion Glory is the name of the weapon equipped by outstanding F.O.S. graduates. Its name originates from the lion-like deep roar when it is swung. Lions are not easily tamed, and Lion's Glory is not lightly given out. Holders need to discipline themselves and engrave their hopes on their chests to be worthy of the glory of the lion's soul.

Name: Palm Snow
Description: Oathbound — Cannon
WorldDesc: Snowflakes melt in the palm of your hands, and passion raises the temperature between your fingers. Together, you will no longer be afraid of the cold winter.

Name: Shadowforged — Dying Light
Description: Festival — Katana
WorldDesc: With only traces of material applied in a special coating process, this blade has a crimson glow like a setting sun. It has no real impact on the weapon's performance, but somehow it gives an impression that the blade is sharper under the effect of this amazing color.

Name: Open Annulus
Description: New Life — Amplifier
WorldDesc: The internal transmission loop of Open Annulus is complex and esoteric because of its avant-garde notch design. Once considered to prioritize form over function, its immense computing power has silenced its naysayers as its processing power reaches new heights from its breakthrough innovation.

Name: Platinum Swan
Description: Advanced Production — Levi-Gun
WorldDesc: Just like how people tend to ignore the aggressiveness of swans for their gorgeous looks, the elegant and slender shape of this Levi-Gun often makes others forget the fact that it is a weapon used by Task Force Constructs.

Name: Bonescale Blade
Description: Ocean Secret — Katana
WorldDesc: Do you really think mermaids have no means to protect themselves? They forge their scales into a mail and bones into a blade to defend their bodies, minds, and their important ones behind.

Name: Shark Fang
Description: Ocean Secret — Chainsaw
WorldDesc: Aloha! Shark incoming! What do you mean that's not how sharks sound? Don't nitpick the details, c'mon! —NA-NA-MI, having gone full shark mode

Name: Moonlight Fantasia
Description: Festivals — Uniframe Cello Blade
WorldDesc: Away from the familiar roads and into the mysterious night. Close your eyes and let the silent music of the night flow, soft and bright. This may not be the home you yearn for, nor the end of your journey. Even so, rest my little traveler, just for a while and lose yourself in this symphony of lights.

Name: Firmament
Description: Wandering Ballad — Scepter
WorldDesc: In the vast cold sky, this is the only thing that never leaves the deity's side. What is she waiting and wishing for? It seems that only the ones who can reach her will know the truth.

Name: Giggling Pumpkin
Description: Hallow Collection — Saw
WorldDesc: What would the world be like if there were no laughter for a festive celebration? Give me a pumpkin... Like this... and this... See, how big is its smile!

Name: Gray Moon Embrace
Description: Paradise Lost — Gunblade
WorldDesc: A weapon that cuts through the red tide as if desiring to drink all the blood of its enemies. As long as its hilt is gripped tightly, its wielder will have an endless impulse to keep moving forward no matter what has happened. But is this an eternal curse or a voluntary choice of its wielder?

Name: Oceanic Assault
Description: Ocean Secret — Greatsword
WorldDesc: A sword that uses a massive amount of soft filling material to cope with impact beyond the limit. Its unique design also makes it look more like a cushion than a weapon. Although the cold light reflected by the blade (the fin) makes most people drop the idea of holding it while sleeping, the fish's eyes are surprisingly mesmerizing. Even the designer ended up falling victim to it.

Name: Flame Beast
Description: Operation Zero — Cannon
WorldDesc: Although the user always complains that the designer misunderstood their requirements and that they want a feline beast who devours food, not a cute beast who holds a knife and fork, the user has never raised the appeal or asked for adjustment.

Name: Birth at Silent Night
Description: New Life — Uniframe Glaive
WorldDesc: A loyal white dog builds the path between life and death. An elegant black cat chases away the evil serpent. She wields the scepter in her hand and prays for all her people to have hope in life.

Name: Nightflyer
Description: Spring Festival — Bow
WorldDesc: A bow that follows the style of a traditional hunting bow both in terms of design and crafting techniques. Its black gold body and faintly glowing red dots on it can always make one think of a hunter in an ambush. Preys will always fall at the sound of the bowstring.

Name: Shadow Blade
Description: Spring Festival — Greatsword
WorldDesc: A greatsword featuring a low-key dark color scheme to highlight the durability of its material. However, its user commented, "The color is too dull. It needs something vibrant." Therefore, a red ribbon was added to the sword. Besides, the ribbon is surprisingly suitable for the festival that we are celebrating.

Name: Spring's Rising
Description: Spring Festival — Scepter
WorldDesc: Set off the firecrackers to chase away the evil and welcome the spring. In the light of the firecrackers, people wish one other a happy, prosperous new year.

Name: Black Sheep
Description: New Life — Dual Guns
WorldDesc: If we only see ourselves through the lens of our mistakes, we may naturally label ourselves as "black sheep." However, no one is eternally trapped in the past. A fired bullet will be set on a new target, and even the "weapon" will regain its true colors.

Name: Blue Slumber
Description: Yesterday Once More — Uniframe Chain Blade
WorldDesc: A dreamy blue rose blooms in the palm of the knight's hand. There he stands, on the shore far across the distance, praying for the dream world to extend and the pedals to crush the confusion and lead a way for an encounter. Even if the connection is bound to be made with thorns, and despite the suffering and the pain, he will never let it go until death.

Name: Shining Banner
Description: New Life — Banner Spear
WorldDesc: A flag embodies willpower and ideals. Its design is simple, but the spirit of solidarity it carries can truly reach the hearts of anyone. It will shine forever as long as there are people willing to unite and keep fighting for the victory of humanity!

Name: Red Blossom
Description: New Life — Uniframe Dragon Axe
WorldDesc: The girl on the stage nervously holds her hands before her chest, while the audience eagerly anticipates hearing her singing. She makes up her mind and draws an arc with two fingers. Just when the audience is about to imitate her gesture, a red, sharp blade appears and starts dancing in sync with the girl. After a short silence, the audience bursts into cheers—Being good at singing is not the only standard for the new generation of idols.

Name: Dragonboat
Description: Dragon Boat Festival — Uniframe Greatsword
WorldDesc: A greatsword created with the theme of an ancient Dragon Boat Festival celebration ceremony. A tester complains that a sword with this design can only be an exhibit and then raises the sword, which immediately breaks the wall of the testing room.

Name: Theros' Bloom
Description: Beats & Beach — Banner Spear
WorldDesc: In order to protect the maiden from the scorching light, its panels open as if a flower blooms, occupying a space exclusively for her. Maintaining a low profile, the maiden looks for something that can arouse her interest along with the flow of music, until a person meets her gaze and instantly turns away. The maiden knows it is time to use its another function. She folds the panels down and hurls it like a javelin. It pierces into the ground right before the commandant.

Name: Titania
Description: Wandering Ballad — Scepter
WorldDesc: Butterfly wings carry dreams and give off a jade-colored luminescence. As long as the traces of memory do not fade, the light of the scepter will not grow dim, and the magic of realizing dreams will last forever.

Name: Southern Cross
Description: Mistletoe — Swordstaff
WorldDesc: As the daylight fades, the stars of the cross appear in the night sky, leading those who have been lost back to the right path.

Name: Soaker Mk.81 Redux
Description: True Blue — Gun Set
WorldDesc: Soaker Mk.81 was originally just a toy sold by a certain 13th consortium during the Golden Age. It is surprising that it can really be used as a weapon after Wanshi's thorough modification. Equipped with Wanshi's customized energy can filled with mint-flavored gas, it can refresh the minds of its user and the target hit when it fires. It also retains a function that a toy should have. By reducing its power output, its user can blow away sleepiness with pleasantly cool winds.

Name: Crimson Banner
Description: Horizon — Spear Shield
WorldDesc: The knight rides on her track at dawn. She will share her victory with you. Let the glory of triumph burn on the flag high above the podium.

Name: Lunar Clouds
Description: Festivals — Amplifier
WorldDesc: I stand against the railing in the wind under the moon, mourning over my hometown which has long been destroyed.

Name: Elpis, Release!
Description: Fantasy Harmony — Bow
WorldDesc: Carrying the purest dream of the girl, the pink bow spreads its wings to shoot the arrow infused with passion and hope to the darkness before dawn. When the dawn breaks, the girl travels in the sound of discussion and sees the familiar figure. She secretly pulls the pink bowstring that not only contains the power to destroy evil but also Cupid's magic.

Name: Leisure Time
Description: New Life — Gunblade
WorldDesc: The new version modified based on Kara Type I. It's lighter, more flexible, and easy to hide. Obviously, he is prepared to protect the other person in any situation.

Name: Woe's Wonder
Description: Paradise Lost — Composite Armaments
WorldDesc: Though covered in the dark blood of the past, the hunter still holds the weapon in his hand tight. No one needs to know what he sacrificed. He steps on the path of bodies and will bring the silver lining as promised at the end of the night.

Name: Dawn's Judgment
Description: Gilded Glamor — Amplifier
WorldDesc: The forgotten goddess has retrieved her lost power and will walk to the dawn with her own will.

Name: Wind Wisher
Description: Ephemeral Euphony — Flute Sword
WorldDesc: I pray for you and may the gods hear my prayer. The girl sitting quietly in the courtyard blows her flute softly. May all the happiness in the world always be with the one she has been missing in a faraway place. The flute music. The sound of the fallen leaves. A gaze through the dancing snow into the mist. "Can I see you again even just for a moment...?"

Name: Light Silk
Description: Festival — Levi-Gun
WorldDesc: The spring breeze blows the leaves, at the other end of the hackberry woods, a beautiful lady is waiting for you.

Name: Serum Bundle (S)
Description: Gives 30ml of Serum.
WorldDesc: Small Serum bundle for the Commandant's use. Holds a small amount of Serum.

Name: Serum Bundle (M)
Description: Gives 60ml of Serum.
WorldDesc: Medium Serum bundle for the Commandant's use. Holds a moderate amount of Serum.

Name: Serum Bundle (L)
Description: Gives 120ml of Serum.

Name: Serum Bundle (XL) [abandoned]
Description: Gives 180ml of Serum. [abandoned]
WorldDesc: Extra large Serum bundle for the Commandant's use. Holds a huge amount of Serum.

Name: Serum Bundle (XXL) [abandoned]
Description: Gives 240ml of Serum. [abandoned]
WorldDesc: Double extra large Serum bundle for the Commandant's use. Holds a massive amount of Serum.

Name: Cog Pack (S)
Description: Gives 10000 Cogs.
WorldDesc: A box of Cogs that has become far more valuable than could ever be imagined, now that it is known that they contain a compound crucial for Construct creation.

Name: Cog Pack (M)

Name: Serum Chocolate
Description: Gives 30ml of Serum.
WorldDesc: A chocolate box seems to be produced by the Babylonia market street, but the handmade Serum label on the top left corner shows that it is actually made by the giver.

Name: Equipment Overclock Black Box (S)
Description: Gives random equipment overclock materials.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Minor HQ Black Box
Description: Gives a random Lv.45-50 HQ Facility.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Equipment EXP Set (S)
Description: Gives random energy materials for enhancing equipment.
WorldDesc: Equipment enhance module issued by Babylonia. Requires authentication of the Commandant's identity to open.

Name: HQ Black Box (M)
Description: Gives a random Lv.55-60 HQ Facility.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Lucky Chest
Description: A red envelope worthy of 180,000 Cogs. Share it with other members!  Share Cogs to unlock the corresponding [Cat Grab] member.
WorldDesc: Humph. So this is the chest. Nanami also has some ready this year!——Diary No.5066, Nanami

Name: F.O.S. Instructor Medal
Description: Issued to commandants who have their students successfully graduated. The number on it represents the number of graduates. See the Collection Wall for more details.

Name: Tantalum Ore
Description: Can be exchanged for various rewards in the shop. Available through Norman Revival Plan.
WorldDesc: Tantalum-193 is one of the vital components of Construct technology. Back in the Golden Age, majority of Tantalum came from Tantalum Ores. Mining and refining of Tantalum Ore therefore became Norman International's main business over time.

Name: Autonomous Miner
Description: The Autonomous Miner will collect a fixed amount of ores every day. Clear the [Elimination battle] of Norman Revival Plan to increase the base number of miners.
WorldDesc: A mining robot developed by Norman International. With a simple structure, it is able to perform with great stability, and has the ability to self-multiply using universal parts.

Name: 6★ Weapon Resonance Shard
Description: Can be exchanged for 6★ Weapon Resonance materials from the exchange shop.
WorldDesc: Contains multiple encrypted data string fragments, which combine and compile when they come into contact with each other, forming complete Weapon skill strings.

Name: Electricity
Description: Used to improve the overall combat effectiveness of echelon. It can be obtained from Norman Revival Plan Power Station.
WorldDesc: Electricity has existed as the most universal energy since it was discovered, and it is not an exaggeration to say that it is the cornerstone of human civilization supporting the entire Golden Age. At that time, the metallurgical mining industry, led by Norman, needed a lot of electricity.

Name: Gift for Instructor - Memory
Description: Obtained when the instructor reaches 100 Mission Activity. The instructor can then gift it to students who complete the guide mission. It can be obtained three times a day, and they are cleared every week.
WorldDesc: Special rations from F.O.S. Military Command College have been carefully packaged as gifts by instructors to encourage serious students in their collaborative programs.

Name: Marg
Description: Use Margs to purchase items in Interval Preparation Shop.
WorldDesc: Is that you, Marguerite, is that really you? Answer me, answer me!—The Jewel Song

Name: Inspiration
Description: Can be used in Behind the Curtain
WorldDesc: The creative magical download from the universe unconsciously.

Name: Cadenza
Description: Can be used in Rehearsal
WorldDesc: A beautiful improvised musical passage!

Name: Neume
Description: Use Neumes to exchange for items in the Memento Hall
WorldDesc: Neumes are another significant development in medieval music history in addition to Gregorian chant.

Name: Sacred Sword
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: It is not the sacred sword that makes one a hero. It is a hero that makes a blade a sacred sword.

Name: Playwright's Notebook
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: A carefully preserved notebook that has a mixed fragrance of oil ink and a faint fragrance with documents between pages.

Name: Portrait of the Princess
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: The hero who defeats the dragon will...

Name: Prayer
Description: A Recitativo di Fantasia collectible
WorldDesc: Every story has an ending. What's your opinion on how it ends for the girl in the portrait named "Prayer"? Do you want her to have a better ending or just let the story end like this? Regardless of your choice, you can always rewrite the ending of the story as long as you have that prayer in your heart.

Name: Silver Bell
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: A silver bell with mysterious power. At first, you only used it as a charm. However, if you shake it slightly, it will produce a sound that can confuse every enemy that has a mind.

Name: Gem
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: A gem buried in ash. We don't know its function or worth.

Name: Magic Pipe
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: A pipe full of magic. When it is played, the pipe can bring mutually exclusive souls together and connect kindred spirits. Everything is between the virtual and the reality.

Name: Thank You Gift
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: A thank you gift from the villagers to the hero who helped them.

Name: Music Score of The Song of Siren
Description: Recitativo di Fantasia Item
WorldDesc: A music score that records The Song of Siren that is sung by a girl traveler according to the sailor.

Name: Expedition Supplies
Description: Supplies in the Guild Expedition. Use them to move around on the field or attack target locations.
WorldDesc: During the Guild Expedition, <color=#4169E1>70</color> Expedition Supplies will be restored daily at <color=#4169E1>20:00 (UTC)</color>. You can store up to <color=#4169E1>210</color> Expedition Supplies.

Name: Expedition Loot
Description: Loot obtained after the Guild Expedition I. Use it to exchange for items in Shop.
WorldDesc: Season 1 event shop will <color=#4169E1>permanently close on Nov 9</color>. Please exchange for items before it closes.

Name: Computing Power
Description: An Extremis Collaboration event item
WorldDesc: An item that enhances a frame's overall processing capacity. Use it in Extremis Collaboration - Talent.

Name: Downfall Crystal
Description: Obtained after the adventure result calculation. Use it to increase the Reward Level and obtain the mode reward. (Excess Downfall Crystals won't be kept when Curse Queller's Path reaches the max level.)
WorldDesc: A crystal formed by catastrophes. The ethereal prayer will become the food for your mind.

Name: Curse-Dispelling Chapter
Description: Obtained following the adventure result calculation. Use it to enhance the Lost Apocrypha to a higher phase and permanently boost the characters' abilities during the journey.
WorldDesc: A fragment of lost knowledge. Let the ancient wisdom lead you to the depths of the world.

Name: Tinbread Cookie
Description: Tinbread Cookies can be used in adventures to purchase items in "Shark-speare Sale" or do trades in events. Cannot be carried over to a new run.
WorldDesc: Cookies made with tin according to the taste of a legendary demon. They've been used as a common currency after the Mythical Age.

Name: Biomimetic Blood
Description: Biomimetic Blood can be used in adventures to restart battle, revive characters, or even do trades in events. Cannot be carried over to a new run.
WorldDesc: An elixir the church made with the ancient knowledge left behind. It has an outstanding therapeutic effect on most common injuries.

Name: Expedition Loot II
Description: Loot obtained after the Guild Expedition II. Use it to exchange for items in Shop.
WorldDesc: Season 2 event shop will <color=#4169E1>permanently close on Nov 9</color>. Please exchange for items before it closes.

Name: Achievement Points
Description: Used to indicate progress toward course completion. Reach certain Achievement Points to unlock higher-level License Upgrade Exams.
WorldDesc: Reach the required Achievement Points to unlock the corresponding exams.

Name: Astro-Mystery Box
Description: Use it to unlock exclusive story in the "Starry Night Astrology".
WorldDesc: A handmade mystery gift box. One has to try hard to suppress the temptation to shake it. "Isn't it more romantic to share it with the one you love?"

Name: City Art Badge
Description: Can be exchanged for items in the Palette Clash Shop.
WorldDesc: Awakened machines designed and produced this metal badge to award the individuals who have made outstanding contribution to Constellia's art.

Name: Focus Logic
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Consists of passive skills that enhance DMG and increase durability. Suits those who prefer a single type of weapon.

Name: Parallel Logic
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Parallel Logic allows Trailblazer to equip two weapon modules at the same time. Suits those who prefer a flexible combat style.

Name: Starfall
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Each skill cast accumulates 1 stack of energy. Once there are 6 stacks, Starfall can be cast to pull in enemy units in a large area, dealing 3500% Physical DMG in total. Dodging and the 3rd/6th hit of Basic Attack can also accumulate energy stacks.

Name: Fist Barrage
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Tap the Signature button to consume 100 Signature Energy, charge for a brief moment, then unleash multiple rapid strikes against the target in front, dealing 3500% Physical DMG in total.

Name: Wide-Area Strike
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: After equipping this module, the Base DMG of Energy Weapon Mode will increase by 50% while the Basic Attacks in this mode attack 25% slower. Casting this skill actively will consume 30 Signature Energy to activate the Charge Mode for 5s, during which tapping the Signature button again will unleash a wide-area strike that deals 2000% Physical DMG. Every Signal Orb pinged during the Charge Mode will further increase DMG by 5%.

Name: Star Slasher
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: After equipping this module, Basic Attacks generate 4 more Signature Energy. Every 5m of Lightblade length will increase DMG by 20%. Casting this skill actively will consume 100 Energy to deal 2700% Physical DMG to the enemies in front within the length of the Lightblade.

Name: Fistblade Weapon
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: A weapon module that prioritizes melee attacks. In Fistblade Mode, Trailblazer will use 3 skills with cooldowns.

Name: Energy Weapon
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: A weapon module that utilizes an energy cannon and lightblade. In Energy Weapon Mode, Trailblazer will use 3 different Signal Orb skills.

Name: Exergonic Weapon
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When Focus Energy is full, the next skill's DMG multiplier increases by 100% and will drain all Focus Energy once cast.

Name: Energy Search
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Every 30s, the aerial support will scan the coordinates of Trailblazer and drop a maintenance crate. Picking up the crate will replace the damaged parts, restore 25 Module Stability and temporarily heal 25% of max HP.

Name: Weapon Restructuring
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Allows Trailblazer to equip two weapon modules and switch between them at any time. Each switch will drain all Focus Energy. Upon switching from Fistblade to Energy Weapon, every 10 Focus Energy will generate a random Signal Orb; upon switching from Energy to Fistblade Weapon, every 20 Focus Energy will reduce the cooldown of all skills by 1s.

Name: Energy Search
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Every 30s, the aerial support will scan the coordinates of Trailblazer and drop a maintenance crate. Picking up the crate will replace the damaged parts, restore 25 Module Stability and temporarily heal 25% of max HP.

Name: Block
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When this skill is ready, tap a Red Orb to channel a beam that strikes the target for 700% Physical DMG and Blocks incoming attacks for a brief moment. 6s cooldown. Successful Blocks will interrupt the enemy's attack and knocks it back.

Name: Bullet Punch
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When this skill is ready, tap a Blue Orb to charge for a short duration and dash toward the target, dealing 900% Physical DMG. 8s cooldown.

Name: Rising Punch
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When this skill is ready, tap a Yellow Orb to leap into the air using Anti-gravity Energy, knocking the target in front up with the Fistblade and dealing 1200% Physical DMG. 10s cooldown.

Name: Spinning Lightblade
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Charges toward the enemy and attacks with the Lightblade, dealing 390%/780%/1170% Physical DMG based on the number of orbs pinged.

Name: Lightblade Sprint
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Slashes the enemy with the Lightblade, dealing 680%/1360%/2040% Physical DMG based on the number of orbs pinged.

Name: Cluster Missiles
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Opens the chest missile pod to launch 12 seeking missiles that strike the enemy, dealing 510%/1020%/1530% Physical DMG based on the number of orbs pinged.

Name: Focus Level
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Focus Energy's limit increases by 100% and its DMG Bonus limit increases by 100%. Each combo landed will increase Extra DMG Bonus by 1%, up to 100%. Every skill or Basic Attack cast will restore 1 additional Signature Energy.

Name: Efficient Focus
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Focus Energy charges 50% faster. Each time a skill or Basic Attack hits a target, there is a 30% chance to reduce its cooldown by 1s or gain 1 Signal Orb.

Name: Heated Plunder
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: After eliminating an enemy, Energy Modules will drop randomly. Looting these modules will restore a small amount of Module Stability, but due to their poor compatibility, each module has a 30% chance to break upon entering the battle.

Name: Rotating Combustion
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When any module is damaged, tap this button to change into a backup frame and detonate the original frame for 3000% AOE Physical DMG. 200s cooldown. Airdrops no longer restore Module Stability and HP, but provide spare parts instead. Each airdrop picked up will reduce the cooldown of this skill by 20s.

Name: Weapon Engine
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: 3-Pings also make Trailblazer invincible for 1s. Casting this skill will also cast Blue Orb 1-Ping and benefit from the connected circuit effect.

Name: Aerial Execution
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When both Signature Energy and Focus Energy are full, activating Trailblazer's Energy Weapon Mode will consume all Signature Energy and Focus Energy to make it airborne. While airborne, Trailblazer can shoot bullets that deal 250% DMG each. When Trailblazer lands again, it will cast Star Slasher.

Name: Overheat
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Enters the Overload Mode. In this mode, Module Stability decreases faster, skill cooldown decreases by 30%, orbs recover 50% faster, and every module damaged increases Trailblazer's DMG by 20%. When there is only one module functioning, skills have no cooldown and 8 Signal Orbs are generated every second.

Name: Evocation
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When any module is damaged, tap this button to change into a backup frame and detonate the original frame for 3000% AOE Physical DMG. 200s cooldown. Airdrops no longer restore Module Stability and HP, but provide spare parts instead. Each airdrop picked up will reduce the cooldown of this skill by 20s.

Name: Blast Reaction
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: After a successful Block, Trailblazer will return some incoming DMG back to the attacker, then leaps into the air and slams down, dealing 500% Physical DMG in a small area. The next skill has a 30% chance to immediately execute the enemy unit. (Invalid against Boss enemies.)

Name: Veteran
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: A successful Block will fully restore Dodge Gauge and make Dodging no longer consume Dodge Gauge within 8s. The next skill's DMG increases by 100%.

Name: Hand of Annihilation
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Block is replaced with Snap Shockwave that annihilates all missile attacks in a large area, knocks back all enemy units and recovers 40 Signature Energy (with a bonus 2 Signature Energy from each missile annihilated). Cooldown increases by 6s.

Name: Penetrating Punch
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: After charging for a brief moment, dashes toward the target and deals 1200% Physical DMG to all the enemies in a straight line with the Laser Cannon on the arm. Casting this skill has a 30% chance to reset its cooldown.

Name: Evading Stance
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Tapping a Blue Orb after Dodging will remove the charge time and reduce the skill cooldown by 2s.

Name: Suction Punch
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Press and hold the Blue Orb to charge for 3s, then pull in enemy units within 6m. Cooldown increases by 8s. Recovers 20 Signature Energy.

Name: Rising Power
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Hitting a target with less than 30% HP will knock it away and eliminate it directly. (Invalid against Boss enemies.)

Name: Rising Slam
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Hitting a Rising Punch has a 30% chance to trigger a slamming attack, dealing 750% Physical DMG. After casting this skill, restores 2 Signature Energy per second for 5s.

Name: Consecutive Punches
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Hitting a Rising Punch has a 30% chance to trigger an aerial combo, dealing 750% Physical DMG in total. Cooldown increases by 6s. Restores 40 Signature Energy.

Name: Hover Shield
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Not yet available

Name: Quick Charge
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Casting Red Orb 3-Pings repeatedly within 5s will increase the DMG of Red Orb 3-Pings by 50% and allow it to be cast faster. This effect stacks up to 3 times.

Name: Helium Flash
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: When a Red Orb 3-Ping is glowing, press and hold Basic Attack at the right time to trigger a Helium Flash, consuming all Red Orbs to increase Extra DMG by 60% for every additional Red Orb consumed.

Name: Hover Field
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Not yet available

Name: Energy Recycling
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Pinging a Yellow Orb will consume all available Yellow Orbs instead. Each Yellow Orb pinged deals 680% Physical DMG and increases Extra DMG Bonus by 20% for 3s. This duration is reset each time a Yellow Orb is pinged.

Name: Extended Lightblade
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Each Yellow Orb 3-Ping increases the length of Lightblade by 5m, up to 15m.

Name: Hover Supply
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Not yet available

Name: Guided Missile
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Pinging a Blue Orb will consume all available Blue Orbs to deal 510% Physical DMG for each orb pinged and summon missile support for 3s (stackable), launching guided missiles at the enemy every 1.5s.

Name: Heat Unleashed
Description: Trailblazer Modification
WorldDesc: Blue 3-Pings will consume all Focus Energy. Every 100 Focus Energy will increase the Lightblade by 10m, up to 15m. Also launches missiles to the enemy unit.

WorldDesc: According to the records, it was a delicacy that people in the Golden Age made and enjoyed elaborately for special festivals. 'Babylonia' made the serum in that style based on the recipe.

Name: [Christmas Cabin] Blueprint Bundle
Description: Gives a full set of [Christmas Cabin] Decor Blueprint.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: [Christmas Cabin] Set
Description: Gives a full set of [Christmas Cabin] Decor.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: [Christmas Cabin] Blueprint Pick
Description: Choose 1 of the [Christmas Cabin] Decor Blueprints.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: A-Rank Construct Pick
Description: Choose one from 11 A-Rank Constructs: Dawn, Lux, Palefire, Zero, Blast, Nightblade, Astral, Bastion, Brilliance, Silverfang, Arclight.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: S-Rank Inver-Shard Pack
Description: Choose one from the following 7 S-Rank Constructs to obtain [Inver-Shard *6] : Entropy, Luminance, Tenebrion, Pulse, Ember, Crimson Abyss, Veritas.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: Babylonia Supply Pack
Description: Babylonia will airdrop supplies to the operation squads under certain special circumstances.
WorldDesc: Randomly gives a set of the following rewards: Basic Construct R&D Ticket x100, Serum Bundle (M), Coating Sketch x20, Serum Bundle (S), Weapon Enhancer IV x2, Memory Enhancer IV x2, Precious Gift Box, Cogs x10000.

Name: A-Rank Construct Pick
Description: Choose one from 12 A-Rank Constructs: Dawn, Lux, Palefire, Zero, Blast, Nightblade, Astral, Bastion, Brilliance, Silverfang, Arclight,Rozen.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: Flaming Egg
Description: A warm Easter egg. Seems there's a new life under the shell?
WorldDesc: Use it to get Cog *30000 and randomly get Event Construct R&D Ticket *5/*10/*15.

Name: Cobalt Egg
Description: An Easter egg made of metal. It's as solid as a weapon.
WorldDesc: Use it to get Cog *30000 and randomly get Targeted Weapon R&D Ticket *5/*10/*15.

Name: Green Egg
Description: An Easter egg can only be found in the bush!
WorldDesc: Use it to get Cog *30000 and randomly get Targeted Weapon R&D Ticket *10 or Event Construct R&D Ticket *10.

Name: Egg Coin
Description: Silver coin engraved with Easter egg pattern. Who cast them remains unknown. It is said that a mysterious hawker will collect these coins in Babylonia at specific festival.
WorldDesc: Exchange for event items at Easter Egg Hawker.

Name: Bunny Coin
Description: Glittering gold coin engraved with bunny pattern. Someone tried to give them to Commandant, claiming they are "Dorm Coins" but was found out by others soon.
WorldDesc: Exchange for event items at Easter Egg Hawker.

Name: Bunny Clay Pot
Description: It can't tell you anything. Afterall, it's just a bunny.
WorldDesc: Use it to get Kuroro Totem *1, Mona Celica *1 and Celica with Pearl Earrings *1.

Name: Square Chip
Description: Can be used to flip one tile in Summer Flip.
WorldDesc: An exquisite square chip, used as a token for the wildly popular board game in the central arcade in Venus Splash Park. Win a certain amount of them and you get to take home all the prizes sealed away in the glass cabinet. Want to try your luck?

Name: One-Point Dice
Description: Can be used in Summer Flip. Allows you to select a reward icon and move it one tile.
WorldDesc: A beautifully crafted six-sided dice, used in the board game in the central arcade of Venus Splash Park. All its six sides bear the same number: "1"—so no matter how you throw it, you will always wind up moving one step.

Name: S-Rank Construct Pick
Description: Choose one from 9 S-Rank Constructs: Luminance,Entropy,Ember,Tenebrion,Pulse,Crimson Abyss,Veritas,Plume,Rigor.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: Construct R&D Surprise Red Envelope
Description: Open the red envelope to gain a random amount of Event Construct R&D Tickets.
WorldDesc:
·10% chance to gain Event Construct R&D Tickets x250
·15% chance to gain Event Construct R&D Tickets x225
·20% chance to gain Event Construct R&D Tickets x200
·25% chance to gain Event Construct R&D Tickets x175
·30% chance to gain Event Construct R&D Tickets x150

Name: S-Rank Construct Pick

WorldDesc: S-Rank Constructs available for selection: Luminance, Entropy, Ember, Tenebrion, Pulse, Crimson Abyss, Veritas, Plume, Rigor,  Laurel and Glory.

Name: Cell Battery EX
Description: For activating Detectors in Energy Detector
WorldDesc: A cell battery with some lingering power. Can be used to activate Detectors.

Name: Rainbow Card
Description: Premium card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Premium card that can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Managed by the Commandant.

Name: Secret Pact Card
Description: Used to research event items.
WorldDesc: Tickets issued to Executor Squads. Accumulate them to access Coating research facilities.

Name: Terminal Code
Description: Event item for [Volatile Priestess] event.
WorldDesc: An access code for the mysterious [Volatile Priestess] event. Rumors speak of neon visions being seen—ghosts of a long-haired maiden in austere prayer.

Name: S-Rank Omniframe Pick
Description: Choose one from 14 S-Rank Omniframes.
WorldDesc: S-Rank Omniframes available for selection: Luminance, Entropy, Ember, Tenebrion, Pulse, Crimson Abyss, Veritas, Plume, Rigor, Laurel, Glory, Garnet, Empyrea and Capriccio.

Name: S-Rank Omniframe Pick
Description: Choose one from 16 S-Rank Omniframes.
WorldDesc: S-Rank Omniframes available for selection: Luminance, Entropy, Ember, Tenebrion, Pulse, Crimson Abyss, Veritas, Plume, Rigor, Laurel, Glory, Garnet, Empyrea, Capriccio, Starfarer and Scire.

Name: Whispers Of Valley Pines
Description: An item Qu sent along with the Activation Date mail. Will be archived in Commandant's secret space.
WorldDesc: Along with Qu's reply came an ancient scroll painting of Kowloong. Judging by the signature, this artwork is a millennium old. "In moss and dew, the dawn is bathed. Through veiled art, our souls are weighed. Upon the stones, pure waters rest. Through myriad valleys, pine winds wade." Anyone witnessing its beauty would surely be spellbound. It captures a moment in the Kowloong history, a serenity Qu will always aspire to but never quite reach.

Name: The Fool
Description: An item Nanami sent along with the Activation Date mail. Will be archived in Commandant's secret space.
WorldDesc: A tarot card created by an AI, combining the image of Nanami and "The Fool". To ensure her path will lead to "The World" she wants to see, Nanami is about to begin a long journey.

Name: Church Visit
Description: An item Haicma sent along with the Activation Date mail. Will be archived in Commandant's secret space.
WorldDesc: Play the music video for "Church Visit". Featuring Haicma's synthesized voice, it introduces Church of Machina through a blend of rap, rock, folk, and pop music. Watching it leaves one in a trance for half an hour.

Name: Beats and Beach Record: First Edition
Description: An item No. 21 sent along with the Activation Date mail. Will be archived in Commandant's secret space.
WorldDesc: The CD's cover alone transports you back to the heights of summer passion. Long-forgotten beats and melodies surge to life at its mere sight. Rumor has it, this first edition CD was made exclusively for Beats and Beach attendees, with very limited quantities released to the public. Clearly played numerous times, it seems No. 21 has relived cherished memories with this time and again. Wait... there's a subtle scratch on the back. Could it be... teeth marks?
